VALUES
	(1,1,'Boston','boston','250 Northern Ave','Boston','MA','02210','6179511368','6172213968','6172215708','','','delfriscos.boston@dfrg.com','delfriscos.boston@dfrg.com, dfboston@dfrg.com, vxayavong@dfrg.com, DFBostonPD@dfrg.com',42.349136,-71.039528,'<p>Visit Del Frisco&rsquo;?s in Boston, nestled in the lavish Seaport District development in historical Liberty Wharf. Featuring spectacular harbor views, a sprawling waterfront patio and a grand circular bar, our main dining room is flanked with your choice of deep booths, private and semiprivate dining rooms. The sleek modern interior features a one-of-a-kind art collection designed to create an extraordinary Boston steakhouse experience.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Parking: Valet and public parking available</li>\n<li>Features: Private and semiprivate dining, outdoor seating with harbor views, wine list of over 1,200 selections, wheelchair access</li>\n<li>Dress: Business casual</li>\n<li>Non-smoking</li>\n<li>Payments: Cash, American Express, Diners Club, Discover, MasterCard and Visa</li>\n</ul>','Britany Kirkpatrick ','Anthony Valletta','Derek Barragan','Courtney Kershaw','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Del-Friscos-Double-Eagle-Steak-House/431080266915804','https://twitter.com/Del_Friscos','','61225','8635','https://maps.google.com/maps?q=250+Northern+Avenue,+Boston,+MA+02210&hl=en&gl=us&z=16&vpsrc=0','published','http://media.dfrg.com/_delfriscos/modal/df-LocationMap-boston.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_delfriscos/locations/LocationMap-boston.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_delfriscos/DF_PDmenu/DF_Boston_PDmenu.pdf','',NULL,'<p>Anthony R. Valletta is the general manager of Del Frisco&rsquo;s Double Eagle Steak House in Boston&rsquo;s new Seaport District. He began his career as a managing partner with RARE Hospitality International Inc. after&nbsp;graduating from&nbsp;local Boston&nbsp;University&rsquo;s Hospitality Administration program. Anthony furthered his experience as a sales and marketing director for Planet Hollywood based in London, England covering the European territory.&nbsp;His talents, both from culinary and management perspectives, were quickly recognized, and during his time with RARE, he teamed for the openings of five steakhouses in the New England area.&nbsp;Anthony is widely known for an unwavering dedication to welcoming guests and exceeding their wishes, whether big or small.&nbsp;Anthony works closely with the Boys &amp; Girls Club of South Boston, Boston University&rsquo;s Hospitality Administration School, The Gregg Hill Foundation and the Zoltan Mesko Foundation.&nbsp;Anthony has been an active member of the Boston community since 2001 and continues to do his part to give back to a city that has been an integral part of his success in Boston.</p>',NULL,'<p>As Derek Barragan neared his high school graduation, it was clear that becoming a chef was what he wanted to do. Everyone in his family loves to cook and it is at the center of their times together. A graduate of the Art Institute of Dallas, he started out as a sous chef and through hard work was promoted to the chef de cuisine in 2007. Barragan joined the team at Del Frisco&rsquo;s Double Eagle Steak House in Fort Worth in 2008 and was promoted to executive chef in Boston. His approach to the business is based on memories of times spent cooking with his family. Derek is excited to be a part of the team that introduces Del Frisco&rsquo;s cuisine, culture and hospitality to the Boston area.</p>',NULL),
	(2,1,'Charlotte','charlotte','4725 Piedmont Row Dr., Suite 170','Charlotte','NC','28210','7045525502','7042555959','7042555962','','','delfriscos.charlotte@dfrg.com','delfriscos.charlotte@dfrg.com, dfcharlotte@dfrg.com, vxayavong@dfrg.com, DFCharlottePD@dfrg.com',35.151535,-80.839355,'<p>Del Frisco&rsquo;?s in Charlotte astounds guests with its luxurious interior and sleek decor. Soaring windows with stunning views of the South Park area provide the perfect backdrop for an unforgettable dining experience. The vibrant main dining room of this unique Charlotte steakhouse buzzes with energy, while the second-story mezzanine bar and stunning private wine cellar offer a more intimate experience for our guests.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Parking: Valet</li>\n<li>Features: Private rooms, view, bar, patio/outdoor seating, wine list of over 1,200 selections, wheelchair access</li>\n<li>Dress: Business Casual</li>\n<li>Nonsmoking</li>\n<li>Payments: Cash, American Express, Diners Club, Discover, MasterCard and Visa</li>\n</ul>','Jeffrey Sigala','Rick Cheesman','Bob Kalish','Leila Lachichi','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Del-Friscos-Double-Eagle-Steak-House/431080266915804','https://twitter.com/Del_Friscos','','12523','8604','https://maps.google.com/maps?q=4725+Piedmont+Row+Drive+Charlotte+NC&hl=en&ll=35.15153,-80.839376&spn=0.024562,0.039096&sll=39.912123,-86.110276&sspn=0.009266,0.022745&z=15&vpsrc=6','published','http://media.dfrg.com/_delfriscos/modal/df-LocationMap-charlotte.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_delfriscos/locations/LocationMap-charlotte.png','http://media.dfrg.com/DEL-PD_Dinner_Menu_Charlotte_7-14.pdf','<p>Jeffrey Sigala was born in Denver, Colorado and grew up in the sprawling suburb of Lakewood. Upon graduation from high school, Jeffrey spent two years in technical school, finishing with a degree in Electronics Engineering. Immediately following, Jeffrey realized that he had a passion for the restaurant business where he continued working nights while studying at Metropolitan State University, earning a BA in English. After getting married, Jeffrey moved to Charlotte, North Carolina where his love for wine blossomed while working for Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse. This eventually led to his current position as wine/beverage manager at Del Frisco&rsquo;s Double Eagle Steak House.</p>',NULL,'<p>General Manager Rick Cheesman grew up just outside of Charlotte, North Carolina before moving to Tampa, Florida in 1981 to attend the University of South Florida and pursue a degree in Business Administration. Throughout college and continuing after graduation he was employed at a nationally renowned steakhouse, eventually rising through the ranks to become the restaurant&rsquo;s general manager. In 1996, Rick joined the Del Frisco&rsquo;s team and has taken great pride in traveling across the country to assist with the opening of many of Del Frisco&rsquo;s Restaurant Group restaurants &mdash; his favorites being the Sullivan&rsquo;s and Del Frisco&rsquo;s right here in his hometown.</p>',NULL,'<p>Executive Chef Bob Kalish grew up on a farm outside of the coal-mining town of Tamaqua, Pennsylvania. Bob attended East Stroudsburg University to pursue a degree in Hospitality Management. He later moved to Greenwich, Connecticut upon accepting a sous chef position. In 1999, Bob joined the Del Frisco&rsquo;s Restaurant Group sister restaurant Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse as a sous chef and was quickly promoted to executive chef. He became an executive chef with Del Frisco&rsquo;s Double Eagle Steak House in 2006. He has served at new location openings in Charlotte, Boston, Philadelphia and Atlanta, and assisted with the Del Frisco&rsquo;s James Beard Dinner in New York City in 2009.</p>',NULL),
	(3,1,'Dallas','dallas','5251 Spring Valley Road','Dallas','TX','75254','9724909000','9726002686','9726002697','','','delfriscos.dallas@dfrg.com','delfriscos.dallas@dfrg.com, dfdallas@dfrg.com, vxayavong@dfrg.com, DFDallasPD@dfrg.com',32.939625,-96.819191,'<p>Dallas is where Del Frisco&rsquo;?s grew up. Located near the Galleria on the Tollway, this unique Dallas steakhouse features live entertainment and eight elegant rooms for an unforgettable dining experience. Three fireplaces warm the larger upper and lower dining rooms, providing our guests with a truly intimate yet grand dining experience.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Parking: Valet</li>\n<li>Features: Live music, private dining, lounge, wine list of over 1,200 selections, walk-ins welcome</li>\n<li>Dress: Business casual</li>\n<li>Nonsmoking</li>\n<li>Payments: Cash, American Express, Diners Club, Discover, MasterCard and Visa</li>\n</ul>','Ed Lasri ','Gina Cook','David Holben','Cara Volmar ','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Del-Friscos-Double-Eagle-Steak-House/431080266915804','https://twitter.com/Del_Friscos','','20254','8601','https://maps.google.com/maps?q=5251+Spring+Valley+Rd+%E2%80%A2+Dallas,+TX&hl=en&ie=UTF8&sll=39.912123,-86.110276&sspn=0.007982,0.019312&z=10&vpsrc=0','published','http://media.dfrg.com/_delfriscos/modal/df-LocationMap-dallas.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_delfriscos/locations/LocationMap-dallas.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_delfriscos/DF_PDmenu/DF_Dallas_PDmenu.pdf','',NULL,'<p>General Manager Gina Cook was born and raised in San Antonio, Texas. She started her restaurant career at Boudro&rsquo;s on the River Walk. After moving to Fort Worth in 2001, Gina opened the first Central Market in the DFW area. Gina then went to work for Chef Tim Love and did two Trail Drives for the James Beard House. She joined the Del Frisco&rsquo;s team at the Fort Worth location in 2006 as the assistant general manager. In 2010, Gina became the general manager of Del Frisco&rsquo;s in Dallas.</p>',NULL,'<p>Nationally recognized chef David Holben serves as regional executive chef of Del Frisco&rsquo;s Double Eagle Steak House in Dallas. David&rsquo;s skills in the kitchen come from formal training, graduating with honors from the Culinary Institute of America and 30 years of experience cooking in the United States and overseas. He learned the highest level of quality standards working at France&rsquo;s finest Three-Star Michelin Restaurants during a yearlong working scholarship, and then returned to Dallas. Chef Holben has opened five acclaimed restaurants, most famously The Riviera restaurant which earned a five-star rating. Chef Holben&rsquo;s talent for creating flavorful dishes and effectively leading his kitchen staff earned him numerous awards and honors, such as cooking for U.S. Presidents Jimmy Carter and George Bush, and being named &ldquo;Chef to Watch For&rdquo; in Esquire magazine. Since joining Del Frisco&rsquo;s as executive chef in 2003, David was featured as chef for the acclaimed James Beard dinners in both Dallas and New York Del Frisco&rsquo;s locations and represented the James Beard foundation as a chef on the Regency cruise line.</p>',NULL),
	(4,1,'Denver','denver','8100 E. Orchard Road','Denver','CO','80111','3037960100','3035008685','3035321598','','','delfriscos.denver@dfrg.com','delfriscos.denver@dfrg.com, dfdenver@dfrg.com, vxayavong@dfrg.com, DFDenverPD@dfrg.com',39.608711,-104.891037,'<p>The lush interior of Del Frisco&rsquo;?s in Denver reflects its astonishing mile-high surroundings. The restaurant features warm dining spaces appointed with both local stone and classic mahogany throughout to create an ambience unlike any other steakhouse in Denver. Our guests enjoy fine dining with local touches in a grand yet intimate atmosphere. Located in the prestigious Greenwood Village area, it?s the perfect place to reconnect over an intimate dinner.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Parking: Valet</li>\n<li>Features: Private dining, wine list of over 1,200 selections, cigar service</li>\n<li>Dress: Business casual</li>\n<li>Payments: Cash, American Express, Diners Club, Discover, MasterCard and Visa</li>\n</ul>','Aubrey Baker','','Tony Schwappach','Johana Blyth','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Del-Friscos-Double-Eagle-Steak-House/431080266915804','https://twitter.com/Del_Friscos','','29572','8603','https://maps.google.com/maps?q=8100+East+Orchard+RoadGreenwood+Village+,+Colorado+-+80111&hl=en&z=16&vpsrc=0','published','http://media.dfrg.com/_delfriscos/modal/df-LocationMap-denver.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_delfriscos/locations/LocationMap-denver.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_delfriscos/DF_PDmenu/DF_Denver_PDmenu.pdf','<p>In the business since 1992, Aubrey Baker has worked in virtually all front and back of the house capacities imaginable. His career has afforded him the opportunity to educate both his staff and guests, forge relationships and be in &ldquo;the people business,&rdquo; and indulge his love for both food and wine. He draws on the knowledge gained in his time in the kitchen to assist him in his goal to create unforgettable, eye-opening food and wine pairings. At Del Frisco&rsquo;s Double Eagle Steak House since 2002, Aubrey has been the wine director since 2006, with a list of over 1,200 carefully chosen selections.</p>',NULL,'',NULL,'<p>Executive Chef Tony Schwappach was born in Kansas and raised in the BBQ Capital of Kansas City. He started his fine dining career during culinary school with some of the finest nationally acclaimed and award-winning fine dining concepts. Tony shows his passion for great food, his team and the culinary industry through the development of his team and the ones around him. He has been a member of the ACF since 1999 and enjoys spending his free time upland, game bird hunting with his bird dogs.</p>',NULL),
	(5,1,'Fort Worth','fort-worth','812 Main Street','Fort Worth','TX','76102','8178773999','8173856103','8174225623','','','delfriscos.fortworth@dfrg.com','delfriscos.fortworth@dfrg.com, dffortworth@dfrg.com, vxayavong@dfrg.com, FortWorthPD@dfrg.com',32.752121,-97.329659,'<p>In the spirit of Texas, Del Frisco&rsquo;?s in Fort Worth enjoys a dramatic yet intimate atmosphere. Located in the upper west side of downtown near Sundance Square, our warm, romantic mahogany-lined walls showcase hundreds of photographs that capture friends of the restaurant to create an atmosphere unlike any other steakhouse in Fort Worth. Guests can choose from a variety of spectacular dining spaces, including our stunning wine cellar, perfect for hosting memorable dinners.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Parking: Valet</li>\n<li>Features: Private and semiprivate dining, wine list of over 1,200 selections, power bar</li>\n<li>Dress: Business casual</li>\n<li>Nonsmoking</li>\n<li>Payments: Cash, American Express, Diners Club, Discover, MasterCard and Visa</li>\n</ul>','Michelle Dykes ','Greg Kalina','Anthony Felli','Misty Horner','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Del-Friscos-Double-Eagle-Steak-House/431080266915804','https://twitter.com/Del_Friscos','','26131','8602','https://maps.google.com/maps?hl=en&q=812+Main+Street+Fort+Worth+,+Texas+-+76102&ie=UTF-8&hq=&hnear=812+Main+St,+Fort+Worth,+TX+76102&gl=us&ei=BuBRTMWtAoeglAeR3tn9BA&oi=geocode_result&ved=0CBMQ8gEwAA','published','http://media.dfrg.com/_delfriscos/modal/df-LocationMap-fortworth.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_delfriscos/locations/LocationMap-fortworth.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_delfriscos/DF_PDmenu/DF_FortWorth_PDmenu.pdf','',NULL,'<p>Greg Kalina is the general manager of Del Frisco&rsquo;s Double Eagle Steak House in beautiful and culturally rich downtown Fort Worth. He joined Del Frisco&rsquo;s Restaurant Group in August 2006 after a 7-year stint as director of operations for a boutique restaurant group. Active in the community, Greg sits on the boards of A Wish With Wings, Bobby Bragan Youth Foundation, and the Fort Worth Stock Show Syndicate. He has chaired the Big Taste of Fort Worth, benefiting Big Brothers/Big Sisters, for five years and is a director on the board governing the Convention and Visitor&rsquo;s Bureau.</p>','http://media.dfrg.com/Greg_Kalina_headshot.jpg','<p>Anthony Felli is the executive chef at Del Frisco&rsquo;s Double Eagle Steak House in downtown Fort Worth. He developed a love for cooking early on while fulfilling the responsibilities of being the oldest of four siblings. Mealtime became the basis to a lifelong culinary career. Anthony has worked for 22 years in kitchens, having started as a dishwasher at a small family-run Italian restaurant. He worked up through many different positions in a variety of restaurants spanning from Central California to North Texas. Anthony joined the Del Frisco&rsquo;s family in 2006, coming on board as the sous chef. After two years, he was promoted to executive chef and has led the culinary team since. While working with Del Frisco&rsquo;s, Anthony has been recognized by &ldquo;Best Chefs America&rdquo; as a Best Chef and as the winner of the Fort Worth, Texas Magazine &ldquo;Top Chef Challenge&rdquo; 2013.</p>',''),
	(6,1,'Houston','houston','5061 Westheimer Rd, Suite 8060','Houston','TX','77056','7133552600','7135687679','7135689188','','','delfriscos.houston@dfrg.com','delfriscos.houston@dfrg.com, dfhouston@dfrg.com, vxayavong@dfrg.com, DFHoustonPD@dfrg.com',29.740612,-95.464172,'<p>Opulent and romantic, Del Frisco&rsquo;?s in Houston is located in the Galleria shopping complex close to Houston?s lively business and commercial action. The elegant two-story space with sweeping windows offers guests a luxurious dining experience. This location offers guests something you won?t find in any other Houston steakhouse with our New Orleans-inspired &quot;?Lagniappe?&quot; menu.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Parking: Valet and lot</li>\n<li>Features: Private and semiprivate dining, power bar, lunch, wine list of over 1,200 selections, wheelchair access</li>\n<li>Dress: Business casual</li>\n<li>Nonsmoking</li>\n<li>Payments: Cash, American Express, Diners Club, Discover, MasterCard and Visa</li>\n</ul>','Chris Schneider','Zaidi Syed','Steve Haug','Ursula Van Dam','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Del-Friscos-Double-Eagle-Steak-House/431080266915804','https://twitter.com/Del_Friscos','','18298','8605','https://maps.google.com/maps?q=5061+Westheimer+Rd+Suite+8060+Houston+,+TX+-+77056&hl=en&z=17&vpsrc=0','published','http://media.dfrg.com/_delfriscos/modal/df-LocationMap-houston.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_delfriscos/locations/LocationMap-houston.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_delfriscos/DF_PDmenu/DF_Houston_PDmenu.pdf','A native Houstonian, Chris Schneider, has been in the restaurant industry since 2000. He began his career at Perrys Steak House as a dining room manager, with a strong focus on wine. After joining Del Friscos, his passion for wine only grew. Chris has enjoyed learning how to tailor-fit a wine for each guest, based on their specific likes and dislikes.  His goal has been continuing to educate team members and guests alike, in the most exciting industry trends.',NULL,'<p>General Manager Zaidi Syed brings more than 25 years of experience in the restaurant industry. While studying computer engineering at Wichita State University, Zaidi began working in the kitchen for a French restaurant, which sparked his interest in fine dining. For the next few years, he continued to work various jobs within the restaurant industry, moving from line cook to chef to front of house where he became general manager. In 1995, Zaidi joined Del Frisco&rsquo;s Restaurant Group&rsquo;s Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse and spent the next few years traveling and assisting in the opening of multiple locations. In 2010, Zaidi joined Sullivan&rsquo;s in Houston as a general manager. Two years later, he became general manager of Del Frisco&rsquo;s Double Eagle Steak House in Houston.</p>','http://media.dfrg.com/Zaidi_General_Manager1.jpg','<p>Since 1997, Executive Chef Steve Haug has perfected his culinary skills working for the award-winning Del Frisco&rsquo;s Double Eagle Steak House. Steve was introduced to fine dining when he took a part-time job in the restaurant industry while attending college in Florida to pursue a degree in engineering. After two years, Steve moved to Texas and took a job in the kitchen at Del Frisco&rsquo;s Double Eagle Steak House. One year later, he was promoted to sous chef, prompting him to switch his major to hotel and restaurant management, graduating with a bachelor&rsquo;s degree from the School of Merchandising and Hospitality Management at University of North Texas. In 2007, Steve was promoted to executive chef of Del Frisco&rsquo;s in Houston. Throughout his 16-year career with Del Frisco&rsquo;s, Steve has assisted in opening restaurants and training staff at multiple locations, including Charlotte, Boston, Philadelphia and Chicago.</p>',NULL),
	(7,1,'Las Vegas','las-vegas','3925 Paradise Road','Las Vegas','NV','89169','7027960063','7026599773','7026746353','','','delfriscos.lasvegas@dfrg.com','delfriscos.lasvegas@dfrg.com, dfvegas@dfrg.com, vxayavong@dfrg.com, DFLasVegasPD@dfrg.com',36.118000,-115.155609,'<p>Del Frisco&rsquo;?s in Las Vegas offers elegant dining just steps from the famed Vegas Strip. From our unique James Bond Table to our rich mahogany dining rooms, Del Frisco&rsquo;?s follows the tradition of grand steakhouses in true Las Vegas style. Featuring eight private dining rooms, including our stunning wine cellar, this is a truly unique Las Vegas steakhouse. </p>\n<ul>\n<li>Features: Live music nightly, outdoor seating, cigar patio, private dining, sports room, wine list of over 1,200 selections</li>\n<li>Parking: Complimentary Valet</li>\n<li>Dress: Business casual</li>\n<li>Nonsmoking</li>\n<li>Payments: Cash, American Express, Diners Club, Discover, MasterCard and Visa</li>\n</ul>','','Torryn Orriss','Fernando Guerrero','Heather Riggi','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Del-Friscos-Double-Eagle-Steak-House/431080266915804','https://twitter.com/Del_Friscos','','31036','8640','https://maps.google.com/maps?q=3925+Paradise+Road+Las+Vegas+,+Nevada+-+89109&hl=en&ll=36.118013,-115.155602&spn=0.024267,0.039096&fb=1&gl=us&cid=0,0,2364187363466209934&z=15&vpsrc=6','published','http://media.dfrg.com/_delfriscos/modal/df-LocationMap-lasvegas.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_delfriscos/locations/LocationMap-lasvegas.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_delfriscos/DF_PDmenu/DF_Vegas_PDmenu.pdf','',NULL,'',NULL,'<p>With humble beginnings as an 11-year-old exchange student from Mexico City, Mexico, Fernando Guerrero began his culinary career in Houston, Texas. Now, with over a decade of restaurant experience in Las Vegas, he has been with Del Frisco&rsquo;s Double Eagle Steak House for nine years. He has been an integral part of multiple Del Frisco&rsquo;s Double Eagle Steak House and Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille openings across the country. He enjoys creating new and innovative recipes daily.</p>',NULL),
	(8,1,'New York','new-york','1221 Ave. of the Americas','New York','NY','10036','2125755129','6463963291','6463963299','','','delfriscos.newyork@dfrg.com','delfriscos.newyork@dfrg.com, dfnewyork@dfrg.com, vxayavong@dfrg.com, DFNewYorkCityPD@dfrg.com',40.759384,-73.981812,'<div itemscope itemtype=\"http://schema.org/VideoObject\">\n<h2 style=\"display:none\">Video: <span itemprop=\"name\">Del Frisco&rsquo;s Double Eagle Steakhouse New York, NY</span></h2>\n<p><meta itemprop=\"thumbnailURL\" content=\"http://media.dfrg.com/del-friscos-video-thumbnail.png\" /><br />\n<meta itemprop=\"embedURL\" content=\"http:// www.youtube.com/embed/auBwQWS9VaM\" /><br />\n<iframe width=\"420\" height=\"315\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/auBwQWS9VaM\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"\"></iframe> <br />\n<span itemprop=\"description\" content=\"Del Frisco&rsquo;s Double Eagle Steakhouse in New York is located in the heart of Midtown Manhattan featuring floor-to-ceiling windows with breathtaking views, Del Frisco&rsquo;s treats guests to an unforgettable New York steakhouse experience.\" />\n</div>\n<p>Del Frisco&rsquo;?s in New York, an energetic, luxurious three-story restaurant, is located in the heart of Midtown Manhattan, near Times Square, Rockefeller Center and Radio City Music Hall. Featuring floor-to-ceiling windows with breathtaking views of Sixth Avenue and nearby Rockefeller Center, Del Frisco&rsquo;?s treats guests to an unforgettable New York steakhouse experience through our chef-driven cuisine, world-class wine program and unparalleled hospitality.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Features: Private dining, wine list of over 1,200 selections, views, power bar, lounge, cellar</li>\n<li>Dress: Business casual</li>\n<li>Nonsmoking</li>\n<li>Payments: Cash, American Express, Diners Club, Discover, MasterCard and Visa</li>\n</ul>','Jessica Certo','Scott Gould','Elvis Inniss','Deborah Yeom','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Del-Friscos-Double-Eagle-Steak-House/431080266915804','https://twitter.com/Del_Friscos','','42265','8620','https://maps.google.com/maps?q=1221+Avenue+of+the+Americas+New+York+,+New+York+-+10020&hl=en&gl=us&z=16&vpsrc=0','published','http://media.dfrg.com/_delfriscos/modal/df-LocationMap-newyork.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_delfriscos/locations/LocationMap-newyork.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_delfriscos/DF_PDmenu/DF_NewYork_PDmenu.pdf','Jessica Certo began her career with Del Friscos Double Eagle Steak House in 2008 as a server. Spurred by her experiences on the floor at Del Friscos, her wine education began in November 2008 with the Viticulture and Vinification course offered by the American Sommelier Association. By April 2009, her passion for wine was solidified. Over the last five years Jessica has completed the American Sommelier Associations Advanced Blind Tasting course, and the Level 1 Introductory and Level 2 Certificated Sommelier exams through the Court of Master Sommeliers.',NULL,'Scott Gould has worked at Del Frisco&rsquo;s Double Eagle Steak House in New York for 11 years. He has served in every front of house role since. In 2007, he was promoted to general manager. In addition to his day-to-day responsibilities, he is also a regional manager who oversees the first Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille in New York City as well as the Del Frisco&rsquo;s location in Boston.  Prior to Del Frisco&rsquo;s, Scott worked in the financial securities industry trading Emerging Market Debt. A University of Florida graduate, who grew up in suburban Detroit, Scott is an avid runner and loves to cook in his personal time.',NULL,'Elvis Inniss was born in Barbados, West Indies. Once in America, he began his career in Mount Vernon, New York working for a soul food restaurant catering to the locals. It then expanded to the Bronx with Elvis as head cook. Elvis&rsquo;s big break came in the form of a Del Frisco&rsquo;s ad looking for experienced cooks. Here, &ldquo;watching and being trained by great chefs was truly beneficial in the growth of my career. I could never repay those who came before me,&rdquo; says Elvis of his training and mentors. He continues to wow guests and truly loves blending flavors and cultures together on a plate.',NULL),
	(9,1,'Philadelphia','philadelphia','1426-28 Chestnut Street','Philadelphia','PA','19102','2152460533','2152404486','2152595956','','','delfriscos.philadelphia@dfrg.com, gm8680@dfrg.com','delfriscos.philadelphia@dfrg.com, dfphiladelphia@dfrg.com, vxayavong@dfrg.com, DFPhiladelphiaPD@dfrg.com',39.951031,-75.165390,'<p>For an unforgettable dining experience, visit Del Frisco&rsquo;?s in Philadelphia. Located near city hall, inside a historic landmark that was once First Pennsylvania Bank, Del Frisco&rsquo;?s offers an unforgettable Philadelphia steakhouse atmosphere. Magnificent balconies draped in plush red fabric overlook the sweeping main dining room. A breathtaking three-story wine tower serves as the centerpiece of the restaurant. Downstairs boasts private dining and reception areas, including the Vault Room.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Features: Private and semiprivate dining, power bar, wine list of over 1,200 selections wheelchair access</li>\n<li>Dress: Business casual</li>\n<li>Parking: Garage parking nearby | Valet starts at 6p: $18 per car</li>\n<li>Nonsmoking</li>\n<li>Payments: Cash, American Express, Diners Club, Discover, MasterCard and Visa</li>\n</ul>','Jeffrey Mayfield ','Carmen Tedesco','John Stritzinger','Jessica Kiefer','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Del-Friscos-Double-Eagle-Steak-House/431080266915804','https://twitter.com/Del_Friscos','','28588','8680','https://maps.google.com/maps?q=1426+Chestnut+St.,+Philadelphia,+PA+19102&oe=utf-8&ie=UTF8&hq=&hnear=1426+Chestnut+St,+Philadelphia,+Pennsylvania+19102&gl=us&ll=39.950996,-75.165398&spn=0.009064,0.020149&z=14&vpsrc=0&source=embed','published','http://media.dfrg.com/_delfriscos/modal/df-LocationMap-philadelphia.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_delfriscos/locations/LocationMap-philadelphia.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_delfriscos/DF_PDmenu/DF_Philly_PDmenu.pdf','',NULL,'',NULL,'<p>As part Del Frisco&rsquo;s Double Eagle Steak House in Philadelphia, Executive Chef John Stritzinger likes to transport diners to another world. John takes prime cuts of beef to new heights, with his expertly crafted dishes in the heart of Center City. He has worked in the region for nearly 20 years. For nearly a decade, he honed his craft in Del Frisco&rsquo;s sister concept, Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse, in Wilmington, Delaware. He then moved over to Del Frisco&rsquo;s. Here, he prides himself on cultivating a rarified atmosphere where only the best is considered acceptable &ndash; and not just in the kitchen. &ldquo;It&rsquo;s also about the amazing service that our servers give to guests and the energy that our restaurant creates,&rdquo; the chef says.</p>',NULL),
	(10,2,'Anchorage','anchorage','320 W. 5th Ave., Room C-01','Anchorage','AK','99501','9072582882','9073313214','9073313215','','','sullivans.anchorage@dfrg.com','sullivans.anchorage@dfrg.com, SulAnchoragePD@dfrg.com',61.217072,-149.888519,'<p>Welcome to Sullivan&rsquo;?s Steakhouse in Anchorage. Physically located in bustling downtown Anchorage, part of the 5th Avenue Mall, our spirit is near the line between naughty and nice. You can spend the day shopping, then spend the night treating yourself to some of the best food, drinks, music and atmosphere at a one-of-a-kind Anchorage steakhouse. </p>','Alan Hammond','','Jacob Nyman','Kristin George','https://www.facebook.com/SullivansSteak','https://twitter.com/sullivanssteak','','11671','8591','https://maps.google.com/maps?q=320+West+5th+Avenue++Anchorage+,+Alaska+-+99501&hl=en&gl=us&z=15&vpsrc=0','published','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/modal/ssh-LocationMap-anchorage.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/locations/LocationMap-anchorage.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/SLV_PDmenu/SLV_Anchorage_PDmenu.pdf','<p>Alan Hammond is one of the managers of Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse in Anchorage, Alaska in the heart of the downtown area. He began his career as a chef for Schuler&rsquo;s of Michigan. He groomed his culinary and wine knowledge at Baker, a private college in Muskegon, Michigan. While there, he worked for the Thrasher family, the Lester Group of Muskegon, and Harris Hospitality Group. Each group held several different concepts and he played a role in all of them. He left the kitchen when moving into the Sullivan&rsquo;s family and focused his skills in the front of the house, and his love for wine led him to take on the role of sommelier.</p>',NULL,'',NULL,'<p>Jacob Nyman is the executive chef for the beautiful downtown Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse in Anchorage. Jacob is a graduate of the New England Culinary Institute in Montpelier, Vermont and has traveled throughout the United States to expand his culinary experience. Jacob is an avid fisherman and is also passionate about vegetable gardening and home preserving. Chef Jacob likes to utilize fresh, seasonal and local ingredients as much as possible in his cuisine and is a strong supporter of Grown in Alaska produce.</p>',NULL),
	(11,2,'Austin','austin','300 Colorado Street, Suite 200','Austin','TX','78701','5124956504','5122018173','5122018174','5122537304','5122537295','sullivans.austin@dfrg.com','sullivans.austin@dfrg.com, SulAustinPD@dfrg.com',30.265947,-97.745224,'<p>Welcome to Sullivan&rsquo;?s Steakhouse in Austin, located in the fashionable Warehouse District at 3rd and Colorado streets. Enjoy great food, fun drinks, live music and a swinging atmosphere right in the middle of Austin?&rsquo;s world-famous nightlife downtown, a few blocks from 6th Street. Sullivan&rsquo;?s is the perfect Austin steakhouse to ?keep it weird.?</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Come experience our whole new look. We recently renovated and we\'re taking things up an octave.</p>','Michael Bass','Todd Henderson ','Jason Long','Kelsey Hart','https://www.facebook.com/SullivansSteak','https://twitter.com/sullivanssteak','','11737','8501','http://maps.google.com/maps?q=300+Colorado+Street+Austin+,+TX+-+78701&hl=en&gl=us&z=16&vpsrc=0','published','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/modal/ssh-LocationMap-austin.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/locations/SLV-LocationMap-austin.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/SLV_PDmenu/SLV_Austin_PDmenu.pdf','<p>Michael Bass is currently the sommelier of Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse in Austin, Texas. Mike started his restaurant career in Prescott, Arizona at Murphy&rsquo;s Restaurant. After a few years, he moved to Denver, Colorado with the Wynkoop Brewing Company, where he ran the beverage program.&nbsp;Mike welcomes the challenges that both novice and experienced wine drinkers present when talking wine with guests, and he loves to share his passion with them, as well as with his peers and staff.</p>',NULL,'<p>Todd Henderson, a native of Raleigh, North Carolina, has been in the hospitality industry since he got his first job washing dishes as a teenager. After traveling and working in California, Colorado and Yellowstone National Park, he returned to North Carolina where he ran a retail shop and restaurant in the Blue Ridge Mountains. Todd eventually returned to his home in Raleigh, where he operated multiple restaurants for a local hospitality group before landing at Del Frisco&rsquo;s Restaurant Group where he has worked for both Sullivan\'s Raleigh and Austin locations. He has a passion for food and wine, and when he&rsquo;s not tending to restaurants he enjoys playing his guitar and watching football on Sundays.</p>',NULL,'<p>Executive Chef Jason Long began working in restaurants at the age of 14 for his father, who owned several restaurants in Los Angeles and San Diego. He began his professional career with the Wolfgang Puck Restaurant Group, quickly being promoted to saucier. Jason next became a sous chef in San Francisco at the Buckeye Roadhouse, working under the renowned Cindy Pawlcyn. After three years at the Buckeye, he began working at Pacifica Del Mar, as the chef de cuisine. Jason has been executive chef with Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse at two locations, beginning at their Palm Desert location. He has been with the Austin location since 2012.</p>',NULL),
	(12,2,'Baltimore','baltimore','One East Pratt St.  #102','Baltimore','MD','21202','4109625503','4103846019','4103846031','','','sullivans.baltimore@dfrg.com','sullivans.baltimore@dfrg.com, SulBaltimorePD@dfrg.com',39.285889,-76.614182,'<p>Welcome to Sullivan&rsquo;?s Steakhouse in Baltimore, located downtown in the landmark area of beautiful Inner Harbor. Nearby attractions include the stunning National Aquarium as well as the Maryland Science Center, and it is within walking distance of the convention center.  With its proximity to lush parks and stunning open water, Sullivan&rsquo;?s is a prime Baltimore steakhouse for an outstanding night out.</p>','','Adam Evans ','Ben Erjavec','Meghan Milliken','https://www.facebook.com/SullivansSteak','https://twitter.com/sullivanssteak','','29470','8535','http://maps.google.com/maps?q=One+East+Pratt+Street,+Suite+102Baltimore+,+MD+-+21202&gl=us&z=16&vpsrc=0','published','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/modal/ssh-LocationMap-baltimore.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/locations/LocationMap-baltimore.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/SLV_PDmenu/SLV_Baltimore_PDmenu.pdf','',NULL,'','http://media.dfrg.com/remsberg_1.jpg','<p>Benjamin Erjavec brings a wealth of culinary experience and talent to his position of executive chef at Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse in Baltimore, Maryland. Born and raised in Ohio, Ben has been passionate about cooking since the age of 15. After graduating from the Pennsylvania Institute of Culinary Arts in 1999, Ben worked at the Pinehurst Resort &amp; Country Club in North Carolina for over three years, then as an executive chef at a local upscale restaurant and an off-premise catering company. Since joining the Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse family in January 2012, Ben has been featured on numerous Baltimore TV segments.</p>','http://media.dfrg.com/Sullivans_1.jpg'),
	(13,2,'Baton Rouge','baton-rouge','5252 Corporate Blvd','Baton Rouge','LA','70808','2259251161','2252242514','2252242626','','','sullivans.batonrouge@dfrg.com','sullivans.batonrouge@dfrg.com, SulBatonRougePD@dfrg.com',30.425035,-91.135841,'<p>Welcome to Sullivan&rsquo;?s in Baton Rouge where you&rsquo;??ll find yourself surrounded by friends and neighbors looking to cut loose at a Baton Rouge steakhouse unlike any other. Located in the Mid City South area, near Interstate 10 on Corporate Boulevard, you can come in to untie, unwind and uncork with our unbelievable food, signature cocktails and swinging atmosphere at Sullivan&rsquo;?s. </p>','','Leo Verde','Leighton Carbo','','https://www.facebook.com/SullivansSteak','https://twitter.com/sullivanssteak','','11740','8551','http://maps.google.com/maps?q=5252+Corporate+Boulevard+Baton+Rouge+,+LA+-+70808&hl=en&gl=us&z=16&vpsrc=0','published','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/modal/ssh-LocationMap-batonrouge.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/locations/LocationMap-batonrouge.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/SLV_PDmenu/SLV_BatonRouge_PDmenu.pdf','',NULL,'<p>Leo Verde was born In Caracas, Venezuela. He began his career as a dishwasher in New Orleans, working in landmark and historic restaurants like Pastore&rsquo;s, La Louisiane, Commander&rsquo;s Palace, Emeril&rsquo;s, Emeril&rsquo;s Delmonico, and Del Frisco&rsquo;s Double Eagle Steak Houses in New York, Las Vegas and Dallas. He has been at the helm of Sullivan&rsquo;s in Baton Rouge since 2003. Verde is known in the community for his commitment to public service and many charities that he serves and raises thousands of dollars for. Leo sits on the Board of the Epicurean Society and Cystic Fibrosis Foundation and is also very involved with the Junior League and Big Buddy Program. He raised $32,000 for the Cystic Fibrosis Baton Rouge Chapter while running the 2013 Boston Marathon.</p>',NULL,'<p>Executive Chef Leighton Carbo began his culinary career in Baton Rouge while attending college at LSU. After receiving his degree, he attended culinary school at Le Cordon Bleu in Portland, Oregon. While in school, he apprenticed at BlueHour. After graduation, he became sous chef at another Portland establishment, Filbert&rsquo;s. He also spent a summer working at WD-50 in New York. After a four-year stint in Oregon, Leighton decided to return home to Louisiana. Here, he has the ability to cook the food that is close to his heart for the people he loves. He has participated in many fundraising events including The Wine Opener for Cystic Fibrosis every year in November, March of Dimes Signature Chef Auction, as well as many other events for the Baton Rouge Epicurian Society.</p>',NULL),
	(14,2,'Charlotte','charlotte','1928 South Blvd, Suite 200','Charlotte','NC','28203','7043358228','7042514048','7042514050','','','sullivans.charlotte@dfrg.com','SulCharlottePD@dfrg.com, sullivans.charlotte@dfrg.com',35.210087,-80.859795,'<p>Welcome to Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse in Charlotte, located in the Steel Yard Complex of the historic and vibrant South End neighborhood. Surrounded by lush trees, our two-story brick building offers diners an escape from the everyday. Our delicious food, signature cocktails and lively music will make your evening at Sullivan&rsquo;?s a Charlotte steakhouse experience you will not soon forget.</p>','','Mike Palo','Justin Walters','Nicole Watford Daniels','https://www.facebook.com/SullivansSteak','https://twitter.com/sullivanssteak','','11734','8562','http://maps.google.com/maps?q=sullivan%27s+steakhouse&hl=en&sll=35.160479,-80.855467&sspn=0.477717,0.891953&hq=sullivan%27s+steakhouse&t=m&z=11','published','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/modal/ssh-LocationMap-charlotte.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/locations/LocationMap-charlotte.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/SLV_PDmenu/SLV_Charlotte_PDmenu.pdf','',NULL,'',NULL,'<p>Executive Chef Justin Walters grew up in western New York. He graduated from the Pennsylvania Institute of Culinary Arts in 2003 after completing an externship at Grand Harbor Golf and Beach Resort in Vero Beach. Florida. Justin joined Del Frisco&rsquo;s Restaurant Group in 2007 in New York City. He then relocated to the Del Frisco&rsquo;s Steak House in Charlotte as the sous chef before being promoted to executive chef at Sullivan&rsquo;s.</p>',NULL),
	(15,2,'Chicago','chicago','415 North Dearborn','Chicago','IL','60654','3125273510','3122192262','3122192265','','','sullivans.chicago@dfrg.com','sullivans.chicago@dfrg.com, SulChicagoPD@dfrg.com',41.889824,-87.629555,'<p>Welcome to Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse in Chicago. Located in River North, near the Magnificent Mile, Sullivan&rsquo;?s is within walking distance of the Chicago River. Housed in a historic two-story building overlooking Hubbard and Dearborn streets, diners can observe city life bustling below from the main dining room as well as from the private dining rooms for a unique Chicago steakhouse experience. </p>','Ryan Baldwin','Scott Lohr','Jesus Garcia','Janine Bobko','https://www.facebook.com/SullivansSteak','https://twitter.com/sullivanssteak','','11725','8541','http://maps.google.com/maps?q=415+North+Dearborn+Chicago+,+IL+-+60654&hl=en&gl=us&z=16&vpsrc=0','published','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/modal/ssh-LocationMap-chicago.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/locations/LocationMap-chicago.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/SLV_PDmenu/SLV_Chicago_PDmenu.pdf','<p>Ryan Baldwin, sommelier at Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse in Chicago, manages both the restaurant&rsquo;s wine and wine education programs, placing a strong emphasis on the high standards of service. A native of Chicago, Ryan joined the Sullivan&rsquo;s family as a server and bartender in 2008. Two years later, he relocated to France. While living in Paris, Ryan&rsquo;s appreciation for wine and the French wine culture inspired his journey toward becoming a sommelier. Ryan is now an active member of the Guild of Sommeliers, always furthering his education so as to provide guests with welcome, practical advice on partnering interesting wines with Sullivan&rsquo;s distinctive menu.</p>',NULL,'',NULL,'<p>Jesus Garcia, executive chef at Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse in Chicago, never misses a teaching moment for those lucky to learn from him. Born in Mexico City, Jesus immigrated to Chicago in 1984 and began his career with privately owned hospitality giant ClubCorp, where he served in various positions for 25 years, leading to executive chef for the last 10 years of his tenure. This span illustrates Jesus&rsquo;s incredible loyalty, which he has brought with him (along with a sneaky sense of humor and unrelenting ambition) to Sullivan&rsquo;s since joining the team in 2008.</p>',NULL),
	(16,2,'Dallas','dallas','17795 North Dallas Parkway','Dallas','TX','75287','9722679393','','','','','sullivans.dallas@dfrg.com','sullivans.dallas@dfrg.com, dallascatering@steakco.com',32.994202,-96.829666,'','','Shelly Kamer','James Mockerman','Joscelyne Ambrose','https://www.facebook.com/SullivansSteak','https://twitter.com/sullivanssteak','','11731','8506','http://maps.google.com/maps?q=17795+North+Dallas+Parkway+Dallas+,+TX+-+75287&hl=en&gl=us&z=16&vpsrc=0','unpublished',NULL,'http://media.dfrg.com/_delfriscosgrille/locations/LocationMap-default.png','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
	(17,2,'Denver','denver','1745-61 Wazee Street','Denver','CO','80202','3032952664','3032231825','3032232443','','','sullivans.denver@dfrg.com','sullivans.denver@dfrg.com, SulDenverPD@dfrg.com',39.753052,-104.998138,'<p>Welcome to Sullivan&rsquo;?s Steakhouse in Denver. Only a few blocks from Coors Field, Sullivan&rsquo;?s is in the perfect spot for a great evening out. The historic LoDo district of downtown Denver is home to businesses, Union Station and the Museum of Contemporary Art. Sullivan&rsquo;?s is located in the Franklin Lofts building at Wazee and 18th streets, offering a distinctive Denver steakhouse experience.</p>','','Gavin Berry','Daniel Kane','Angela Suppa','https://www.facebook.com/SullivansSteak','https://twitter.com/sullivanssteak','','11689','8503','http://maps.google.com/maps?q=1745-61+Wazee+Street+Denver+,+CO+-+80202&hl=en&ll=39.753063,-104.99814&spn=0.023096,0.039096&gl=us&z=15&vpsrc=6','unpublished','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/modal/ssh-LocationMap-denver.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/locations/LocationMap-denver.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/SLV_PDmenu/SLV_Denver_PDmenu.pdf','',NULL,'',NULL,'<p>Daniel Kane is the executive chef of Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse in downtown Denver, Colorado. He has been a Colorado resident for almost 20 years and received his culinary degree locally, at The Colorado Institute of Art, School of Culinary Arts. Daniel&rsquo;s culinary beginnings were in delis and sandwich shops until the opportunity to move into fine dining was presented. Daniel established a prime steakhouse in Steamboat Springs and became executive chef at a luxury resort hotel. He has been chef and assistant general manager at three different concepts.</p>',NULL),
	(18,2,'Houston','houston','4608 Westheimer','Houston','TX','77027','7139610333','7135706442','7135706459','','','sullivans.houston@dfrg.com','sullivans.houston@dfrg.com, SulHoustonPD@dfrg.com',29.741356,-95.454994,'<p>Located near the Galleria of Houston, Sullivan&rsquo;?s Steakhouse is nestled just inside the 610 Loop, blocks from Highland Village. Rich interiors include an expansive wine cellar, inviting bar and elegant finishes creating a one-of-a-kind Houston steakhouse experience. Make reservations at Sullivan&rsquo;?s of Houston and savor the night.</p>','Kristie Farmer','Steve Weaver ','Horacio Degante','Kristi Beck','https://www.facebook.com/SullivansSteak','https://twitter.com/sullivanssteak','','4661','8504','http://maps.google.com/maps?q=4608+Westheimer+Houston+,+TX+-+77027&hl=en&gl=us&z=16&vpsrc=0','published','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/modal/ssh-LocationMap-anchorage.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/locations/LocationMap-houston.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/SLV_PDmenu/SLV_Houston_PDmenu.pdf','<p>Kristie Farmer started her first wine job bartending at an Italian wine bar called Osteria D&rsquo;Aldo, which served over 100 wines by the glass. From there she moved to Vic and Anthony&rsquo;s Steakhouse where she was given the opportunity to work in the wine department. In 2007, Kristie joined the wine department at the Sullivan&rsquo;s sister restaurant, Del Frisco&rsquo;s Double Eagle Steak House, in Houston. She currently manages Sullivan&rsquo;s list of over 600 wines from 16 different countries and 6 continents.</p>',NULL,'',NULL,'<p>Executive Chef Horacio Degante was born in Cuernavaca, Mexico before moving to Chicago at age seven. While attending school, he worked part-time in the kitchen for a family-owned Italian restaurant. He was promoted to different jobs throughout the kitchen, eventually realizing that cooking was his passion. In 2007, he became sous chef of Sullivan&rsquo;s in Naperville. He later became the sous chef in Houston and in 2012, Horacio was promoted to executive chef in Houston.</p>',NULL),
	(19,2,'Indianapolis','indianapolis','3316 East 86th','Indianapolis','IN','46240','3175801280','3172688968','3172688976','','','sullivans.indianapolis@dfrg.com','sullivans.indianapolis@dfrg.com, SulIndianapolisPD@dfrg.com',39.912994,-86.110733,'<p>Welcome to Sullivan&rsquo;?s Steakhouse in Indianapolis. Located near some of the best shopping in the city at the Fashion Mall of Keystone, you&rsquo;??ll be able to find great styles before dining in style at Sullivan&rsquo;?s. Make your reservation today to flirt with new flavors in a truly unique Indianapolis steakhouse atmosphere designed for an unforgettable night.</p>','Kimberly Vanek','John Stanley','Matt Wahl','Michelle Shryock','https://www.facebook.com/SullivansSteak','https://twitter.com/sullivanssteak','','11713','8502','http://maps.google.com/maps?q=3316+E.+86th+St.+Indianapolis+,+IN+-+46240&hl=en&ll=39.912962,-86.110754&spn=0.046084,0.078192&fb=1&gl=us&cid=0,0,2580249270457432125&z=14&vpsrc=6','published','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/modal/ssh-LocationMap-indianapolis.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/locations/LocationMap-indianapolis.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/SLV_PDmenu/SLV_Indianapolis_PDmenu.pdf','Kimberly Vanek is the wine manager at Sullivans Steakhouse. Kimberly has been a part of the Indianapolis team since the restaurant opened in late 1996. Kimberly always had a passion for wine and is dedicated to enhancing every guests dining experience through wine. She enjoys working with the Indianapolis area Humane Societies and their events, She is a member of the Fishers, Indiana Chamber of Commerce and is a tireless worker in the community.',NULL,'John Stanley is the general manager of Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse in Indianapolis. He began his career as a marketing director in Peoria, Illinois after graduating from Drake University in Des Moines, Iowa. After a successful term with Paragon Steakhouse Restaurants, he has now been with Sullivan&rsquo;s for over 14 years. John was recognized in 2011 by the Hamilton County Visitors Bureau and received the Hospitality Star Award, and he received the Carmel Rotary Club Service Above Self Award in 2012. John is on the Carmel Rotary Club Board and the Northside Nights Board. He is a Free Mason and is heavily involved in making a difference in the community.',NULL,'Executive Chef Matt Wahl became interested in cooking at a young age, cooking alongside his father. He attended culinary school at Sullivan University, graduating in 2005. Later that same year, Matt took a job with Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse, part of the Del Frisco&rsquo;s Restaurant Group. He was promoted to sous chef and relocated to the Sullivan&rsquo;s in King of Prussia, Pennsylvania. He remained on the East Coast for a few years, bringing his skill and enthusiasm to several different Sullivan&rsquo;s locations, opening seven restaurants, before relocating back to Indianapolis. Matt was promoted to executive chef in 2013. His favorite dish to prepare is Slow Roasted Short Ribs with a Guinness Reduction.',NULL),
	(20,2,'King of Prussia','king-of-prussia','700 West Dekalb Pike','King of Prussia','PA','19406','6108789025','6105890038','6105890040','6102557453','6102557467','sullivans.kingofprussia@dfrg.com','sullivans.kingofprussia@dfrg.com, SulKingofPrussiaPD@dfrg.com',40.086540,-75.386673,'<p>Welcome to Sullivan&rsquo;?s Steakhouse in King of Prussia. Within walking distance of the shopping at the King of Prussia Mall, you can find an outfit that will make you feel great on the outside before you savor the decadent food, handcrafted cocktails and lively music that will make you feel good on the inside. Make your reservation today for a King of Prussia steakhouse experience you?&rsquo;?ll never forget.</p>','Eric Kiefer','Tim O\'Brien','','Aja Cramer','https://www.facebook.com/SullivansSteak','https://twitter.com/sullivanssteak','','11728','8522','http://maps.google.com/maps?q=700+West+Dekalb+Pike+King+of+Prussia+,+PA+-+19406&hl=en&ll=40.08651,-75.386682&spn=0.022983,0.039096&fb=1&gl=us&cid=0,0,18406588409037057662&z=15&vpsrc=6','published','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/modal/ssh-LocationMap-kingofprussia.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/locations/LocationMap-kingofprussia.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/SLV_PDmenu/SLV_KOP_PDmenu.pdf','<p>Eric Kiefer is the manager/sommelier at Sullivan&rsquo;s in King of Prussia, Pennsylvania. He graduated from the University of Illinois and also has an MBA from Universitas Nebraskensis in Madrid, Spain, where he lived for 10 years. Eric has over 20 years of experience in various positions at fine dining steakhouses.</p>',NULL,'<p>Tim O&rsquo;Brien is the general manager of Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse in King of Prussia, Pennsylvania. He grew up in Orlando, Florida where he attended the University of Central Florida. He began his hospitality career at 16 and has held various positions from executive chef to general manager at other restaurant companies. Tim joined the Sullivan&rsquo;s team in 2012. Tim and the team in King of Prussia believe in delivering a dining experience that exceeds your expectations.</p>',NULL,'','http://media.dfrg.com/Chef_Eric_Gantz_(3).jpg'),
	(21,2,'Leawood','leawood','4501 119th Street','Leawood','KS','66209','9133450800','9133704738','9133709398','','','sullivans.leawood@dfrg.com','sullivans.leawood@dfrg.com, SulLeawoodPD@dfrg.com',38.912819,-94.635193,'<p>The Sullivan&rsquo;?s Steakhouse in Leawood offers transport to another time and place, where cares are swept away and secrets are both shared and made. Located across the street from the Town Center Plaza on the southeast corner of 119th and Roe, you?ll be able to unwind after a long day of shopping with delectable food, first-class cocktails and swinging live music in a truly unique Leawood steakhouse atmosphere.</p>','Eric Noblet','Lisa Carl','Wesley Boston','Corey Napier','https://www.facebook.com/SullivansSteak','https://twitter.com/sullivanssteak','','24319','8536','http://maps.google.com/maps?q=4501+West+119th+Street+Leawood+,+KS+-+66209&hl=en&fb=1&gl=us&cid=0,0,14179863942480846867&z=16&vpsrc=0','published','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/modal/ssh-LocationMap-leawood.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/locations/LocationMap-leawood.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/SLV_PDmenu/SLV_Leawood_PDmenu.pdf','At Sullivans Steakhouse of Leawood, Eric Noblet works to manage and build the restaurants award-winning wine list. Eric joined Sullivans in 2011 with an extensive background in wine and spirits.  Most recently, he served as the bar manager, sommelier and floor supervisor at Trazo Vino Wine Bistro in Leawood, Kansas. In 2009, Eric became a certified sommelier by the Court of Master Sommeliers and received a specialist in wine (CSW) certification by the Society of Wine Educators. Earlier that same year, he received his Level Three Advanced Certificate from the International Wine Center and graduated at the top of his class with the Wine and Spirit Education Trust.',NULL,'<p>Lisa Carl brings more than two decades of restaurant and hospitality experience to her position as general manager at Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse in Leawood, Kansas. After graduating from the University of Missouri-Kansas City, Lisa went on to work with some of the country&rsquo;s best-known restaurants including Houston&rsquo;s and J. Alexander&rsquo;s. Lisa has held high-level management positions at Bravo Cucina Italiana, Fiorella&rsquo;s Jack Stack Barbecue, and Seasons 52 before accepting her current role at Sullivan&rsquo;s. Lisa is passionate about quality food, restaurants and her community.</p>','http://media.dfrg.com/LisaCarl1.jpg','<p>Executive Chef Wesley Boston brings nearly 15 years of experience working in kitchens of high-profile restaurants across the U.S. to Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse of Leawood. He has developed his talents at restaurants including Maggiano&rsquo;s, The Cheesecake Factory and Bravo Italian. Wesley has participated in community outreach and volunteered in the March of Dimes Chef Auction in fall 2012. As the executive chef of Sullivan&rsquo;s, Wesley aims to produce high-quality, delicious cuisine using seasonal produce from regional farms and purveyors whenever possible.</p>','http://media.dfrg.com/IMG1.jpg'),
	(22,2,'Lincolnshire','lincolnshire','250 Marriott Drive','Lincolnshire','IL','60069','8478830311','8478926188','8478926189','','','sullivans.lincolnshire@dfrg.com','sullivans.lincolnshire@dfrg.com, SulLincolnshirePD@dfrg.com, mnovak@dfrg.com',42.194317,-87.931458,'<p>Welcome to Sullivan&rsquo;?s Steakhouse in Lincolnshire. Dine in decadence and sophistication right in the middle of Lincolnshire. Located near the Half Day Center across from the Marriott Theater, you will be able to enjoy amazing food, drinks, live music and ambience in a Lincolnshire steakhouse that will make you will feel as though you&rsquo;re in another place and time.</p>','Dave Katz','Jason P. Yuhasz','Brian Gray','Maegan Novak ','https://www.facebook.com/SullivansSteak','https://twitter.com/sullivanssteak','','27121','8543','http://maps.google.com/maps?q=250+Marriott+Drive+Lincolnshire+,+IL+-+60069&hl=en&ll=42.194315,-87.93148&spn=0.022256,0.039096&gl=us&z=15&vpsrc=6','published','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/modal/ssh-LocationMap-lincolnshire.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/locations/LocationMap-lincolnshire.png','http://media.dfrg.com/SLV_Lincolnshire_PDmenu1.pdf','<p>Dave Katz was born and raised in Libertyville, Illinois. Dave graduated with a bachelor&rsquo;s degree in psychology with a business administration minor from the University of Iowa. He has always worked in the restaurant industry in some fashion and started with Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse as a server. After having held multiple positions at Sullivan&rsquo;s, Dave was promoted to a manager position and runs the wine program at Sullivan&rsquo;s in Lincolnshire. He is an avid sports fan, with hockey and football being his favorite sports.</p>',NULL,'<p>Jason Yuhasz was born and raised in Indiana. He graduated with an associate&rsquo;s degree in culinary arts from Johnson &amp; Wales University in 1995. Jason has served as executive chef of 82 Queen in Charleston, South Carolina and the Peasant Restaurant Group in Atlanta, Georgia. He has been the general manager at Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse in Lincolnshire since 2011. Jason is the board president for The Greater Lincolnshire Chamber of Commerce.</p>',NULL,'<p>Brian Gray was raised in New Mexico but was born in Chicago. Brian started working in the restaurant industry after many years in construction management. He always had a passion for cooking, which made the transition very smooth. After several years working all areas of the kitchen, Brian was promoted to sous chef at Bravo Cucina Italiana. He came to Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse in 2012 and quickly moved up the ranks to become the executive chef.</p>',NULL),
	(23,2,'Naperville','naperville','244 South Main Street','Naperville','IL','60540','6303050230','6304421748','6304421754','','','sullivans.naperville@dfrg.com','sullivans.naperville@dfrg.com, SulNapervillePD@dfrg.com',41.771702,-88.149475,'<p>Sullivan?&rsquo;s Steakhouse in Naperville will transport you to another place and time. Physically located in the Historic District of downtown, our spirit is near the line between naughty and nice. Sullivan&rsquo;?s offers guests a unique Naperville steakhouse experience with delectable food, fun cocktails and swinging live music, enticing our guests to untie, unwind and uncork.</p>','April Brady','Randy Deguzman','Cien Cid','Casey Dulny ','https://www.facebook.com/SullivansSteak','https://twitter.com/sullivanssteak','','11722','8542','http://maps.google.com/maps?q=244+South+Main+Street+Naperville+,+IL+-+60540&hl=en&ll=41.771696,-88.14949&spn=0.022405,0.039096&gl=us&z=15&vpsrc=6','published','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/modal/ssh-LocationMap-naperville.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/locations/LocationMap-naperville.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/SLV_PDmenu/SLV_Naperville_PDmenu.pdf','April Brady is the wine sommelier and dining room manager of Sullivans Steakhouse in Naperville. She began her career in Iowa as a bartender while pursuing her degree at the University of Iowa.  She fell in love with the hospitality industry while there and has never looked back. In 2003, she moved from Iowa City to Naperville and quickly learned that Sullivans in Naperville was the place to be within the community. After two years of serving and heading up training in Naperville, she accepted the position of dining room manager.  Since working at Sullivans, she has fallen in love with wine because it constantly evolves and you have to constantly educate yourself.',NULL,'Born and raised in Chicago and named after Chicago Cubs catcher Randy Hundley, Randy Deguzman knew early on that he was born to entertain. While working in bars and restaurants to help pay for college, Randy found a passion and fell in love with the hospitality industry. His past restaurant history includes TGI Fridays, Champps Americana, and Bar Louie. Outside of work, Randy loves (hates) to play golf and cook.',NULL,'Executive Chef Cein Cid was born and raised in Mexico City, Mexico. He attended culinary school in Mexico City before moving to Chicago. He began his career at Famous Dave&rsquo;s BBQ in Naperville and also worked as assistant kitchen manager for the Portillo&rsquo;s Group at Key Wester Restaurant. In 1988, Cein became part of the Del Frisco&rsquo;s Restaurant Group team, opening the Sullivan&rsquo;s Naperville location. Cein also went on to help open Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouses across the country before becoming executive chef in Naperville.',NULL),
	(24,2,'Omaha','omaha','222 South 15th Street','Omaha','NE','68102','4023420077','4028194999','4028195009','','','sullivans.omaha@dfrg.com','sullivans.omaha@dfrg.com, SulOmahaPD@dfrg.com',41.258392,-95.936028,'<p>Welcome to Sullivan&rsquo;?s Steakhouse in Omaha. Located on the ground floor of Central Park Plaza in the Historic District of downtown, you can unwind after a long day with one of our signature cocktails in a truly one-of-a-kind Omaha steakhouse while watching the world go by outside our large glass windows. You can then turn your evening into an unforgettable night at Sullivan&rsquo;?s.</p>','','Bob Keller','Thurman Gleb','Lucia Sanchez','https://www.facebook.com/SullivansSteak','https://twitter.com/sullivanssteak','','14668','8532','http://maps.google.com/maps?q=222+S.+15th+St.+Omaha+,+NE+-+68102&hl=en&gl=us&z=16&vpsrc=0','published','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/modal/ssh-LocationMap-omaha.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/locations/LocationMap-omaha.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/SLV_PDmenu/SLV_Omaha_PDmenu.pdf',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Executive Chef Thurman Gleb brings more than 10 years of experience to Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse in Omaha. He began his professional career in Isle of Palms, South Carolina as a sous chef at the Sea Island Grill. He then joined Boudro&rsquo;s in Isle of Palms as chef before becoming chef at the Waterfront Grill at the Ameristar Casino in Council Bluffs, Iowa. Thurman brings passion and enthusiasm to his role as executive chef at Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse.',NULL),
	(25,2,'Palm Desert','palm-desert','73-505 El Paseo, Suite 2600','Palm Desert','CA','92260','7603413560','7605238653','7605238710','','','sullivans.palmdesert@dfrg.com','sullivans.palmdesert@dfrg.com, SulPalmDesertPD@dfrg.com, Sul8570@dfrg.com, Pd8570@dfrg.com, crussom@dfrg.com, kevin.riley@sq1.com',33.719612,-116.382645,'<p>Welcome to Sullivan&rsquo;?s Steakhouse in Palm Desert. You can look forward to unforgettable food, drinks, live music and ambience, all designed to let you untie, unwind and uncork. Physically located in the Shops and Gardens of El Paseo, our spirit is near the line between naughty and nice. You can shop for the latest trends before dining in style at an exceptional Palm Desert steakhouse at Sullivan&rsquo;?s.</p>','','Keith Sansone ','Kevin Favinger','Carolyn Russom','https://www.facebook.com/SullivansSteak','https://twitter.com/sullivanssteak','','11686','8570','http://maps.google.com/maps?q=73505+El+Paseo+Palm+Desert+,+CA+-+92260&hl=en&ll=33.719699,-116.382723&spn=0.024987,0.039096&fb=1&gl=us&cid=0,0,482866703793651145&z=15&vpsrc=6','published','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/modal/ssh-LocationMap-palmdesert.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/locations/LocationMap-palmdesert.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/SLV_PDmenu/SLV_PalmDesert_PDmenu.pdf','',NULL,'',NULL,'<p>Executive Chef Kevin Favinger moved across the country from Philadelphia to Palm Desert in 2009 to take over the reins at Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse in Palm Desert. Starting at age 15, he quickly worked his way up the ranks in the culinary world while earning his college degree. His leadership earned Sullivan&rsquo;s the Palm Springs Life 2010 Best Steakhouse of the Desert award.</p>',NULL),
	(26,2,'Raleigh','raleigh','410 Glenwood Avenue, Suite 100','Raleigh','NC','27603','9198332888','9199140682','9199149657','9195615742','9199149657','sullivans.raleigh@dfrg.com','sullivans.raleigh@dfrg.com, SulRaleighPD@dfrg.com',35.785660,-78.646736,'<p>Sullivan&rsquo;?s Steakhouse in Raleigh offers guests a chance to let go and enjoy an unforgettable evening. This truly special Raleigh steakhouse is located in the Creamery Building in the Glenwood South District of downtown. You can enjoy watching the world outside from the large windows of our two-story brick building while enjoying remarkable food, signature cocktails and swinging live music. Make reservations at Sullivan&rsquo;?s in Raleigh and turn your night up.</p>','Katie Huffman','Chip Bennett','Robert Crawford','Paige Akers','https://www.facebook.com/SullivansSteak','https://twitter.com/sullivanssteak','','6269','8561','http://maps.google.com/maps?q=414+Glenwood+Avenue+Raleigh+,+NC+-+27603&hl=en&gl=us&z=16&vpsrc=0','published','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/modal/ssh-LocationMap-raleigh.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/locations/LocationMap-raleigh.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/SLV_PDmenu/SLV_Raleigh_PDmenu.pdf','',NULL,'',NULL,'<p>Robert Crawford, executive chef at Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse in Raleigh, was born in Auburn, New York. After receiving his associate&rsquo;s degree, he moved to North Carolina and was introduced into the culinary world. He worked in a few restaurants before accepting a position with Del Frisco&rsquo;s Restaurant Group as appetizer cook. During his tenure at Del Frisco&rsquo;s Restaurant Group, Robert decided to attend culinary school at Wake Technical Community College. While in school he worked his way through the kitchen, learning each station. After he graduated with a culinary degree, he was offered a sous chef position. A year later, he was named executive chef. For the last three years, Robert has played an important part in the openings for numerous locations all over. His passion and adventurous spirit have created tons of raving fans around Raleigh.</p>',NULL),
	(27,2,'Seattle','seattle','621 Union St.','Seattle','WA','98101','2064944442','2066392773','2066392776','','','sullivans.seattle@dfrg.com','sullivans.seattle@dfrg.com, SulSeattlePD@dfrg.com',47.610184,-122.333221,'<p>The world will be busy outside while you will be enjoying the good life inside Sullivan&rsquo;?s Steakhouse in Seattle. Located downtown near the Washington State Convention Center on Union Street between 6th and 7th avenues, you can watch the hustle and bustle of downtown from the large windows surrounding our restaurant and enjoy first-class food, signature cocktails and bouncing live music. Sullivan&rsquo;?s offers guests a Seattle steakhouse atmosphere that flirts with the line between naughty and nice.</p>','','Justin Rammer','Zach Martinez','Briana McLaughlin','https://www.facebook.com/SullivansSteak','https://twitter.com/sullivanssteak','','42880','8592','http://maps.google.com/maps?q=621+Union+St.+Seattle+,+Washington+-&hl=en&gl=us&z=16&vpsrc=0','published','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/modal/ssh-LocationMap-seattle.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/locations/LocationMap-seattle.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/SLV_PDmenu/SLV_Seattle_PDmenu.pdf','',NULL,'',NULL,'<p>Executive Chef Zachary Martinez has held every position in the field.&nbsp;He gained culinary passion as an apprentice in many kitchens but was ignited with the opportunity to become a sous chef for both Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse and Del Frisco&rsquo;s Double Eagle Steak House. Zach does not believe in perfection, pushing his team to continually seek new ways to improve efficiency and hospitality.</p>',NULL),
	(28,2,'Tucson','tucson','1785 East River Road','Tucson','AZ','85718','5202994275','5207779756','5207779850','','','sullivans.tucson@dfrg.com','sullivans.tucson@dfrg.com, SulTucsonPD@dfrg.com',32.287285,-110.944176,'<p>Welcome to Sullivan&rsquo;?s Steakhouse in Tucson. Located near St. Philips Plaza on the northwest corner of Campbell and River roads, you can escape the noise and buzz of downtown to enjoy first-class food, signature cocktails and live music in a one-of-a-kind Tucson steakhouse atmosphere. Come in soon to experience an evening of unforgettable enjoyment.</p>','','John Hackett','Giovanni Pace','Lauren Reilly','https://www.facebook.com/SullivansSteak','https://twitter.com/sullivanssteak','','11683','8525','http://maps.google.com/maps?q=1785+EAST+RIVER+ROAD+TUCSON+,+AZ+-+85718&hl=en&ll=32.287423,-110.945005&spn=0.050792,0.078192&gl=us&sqi=2&z=14&vpsrc=6','published','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/modal/ssh-LocationMap-tucson.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/locations/LocationMap-tucson.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/SLV_PDmenu/SLV_Tucson_PDmenu.pdf','',NULL,'',NULL,'<p>Executive Chef Giovanni Pace started his career with Del Frisco&rsquo;s Restaurant Group in May 2013 as the executive chef of Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse in Tucson. He has been in the hospitality industry for 22 years going back to his beginning as a cook at the Ritz-Carlton Hotel in Phoenix, Arizona at the age of 17. Since then, he has worked with groups such as The Capital Grille and others. Giovanni says, &ldquo;Tucson and Sullivan&rsquo;s are a perfect fit for me. Both have been truly hospitable and a welcoming new home for this chef.&rdquo;</p>',NULL),
	(29,2,'Wilmington','wilmington','5525 Concord Pike','Wilmington','DE','19803','3024797970','3027540383','3027540388','','','sullivans.wilmington@dfrg.com','sullivans.wilmington@dfrg.com, SulWilmingtonPD@dfrg.com',39.832085,-75.543327,'<p>Welcome to Sullivan&rsquo;?s Steakhouse in Wilmington. Physically located near Market Square, close to the border of Pennsylvania and Delaware, our spirit is near the line between naughty and nice. Our food and service are first class, while our signature drinks and live music drive inhibitions away. Make your reservation for an evening you won?t soon forget.</p>','Anthony Dougherty','Bill White','Tim Baker','Lauren Sagers','https://www.facebook.com/SullivansSteak','https://twitter.com/sullivanssteak','','11710','8510','http://maps.google.com/maps?q=5525+CONCORD+PIKE+WILMINGTON+,+DE&hl=en&ll=39.832367,-75.543194&spn=0.023069,0.039096&gl=us&z=15&vpsrc=6','published','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/modal/ssh-LocationMap-wilmington.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/locations/LocationMap-wilmington.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_sullivanssteakhouse/SLV_PDmenu/SLV_Wilmington_PDmenu.pdf','Anthony Dougherty joined the team at Sullivans in Wilmington following a two-year stint as service manager at Del Friscos Double Eagle Steak House in Philadelphia. While at Sullivans, he has taken over the wine and beverage program and continues to further his knowledge as he directs an award-winning wine program. Prior to his career with Del Friscos Restaurant Group, Anthony managed a fast-paced restaurant in Jenkintown, Pennsylvania.','http://media.dfrg.com/tony_dougherty1.jpg','<p>Bill White has been general manager at Sullivan&rsquo;s in Wilmington for eight years. Prior to that, he spent five years with Sullivan&rsquo;s in Chicago where he became a Cubs fan. Bill&rsquo;s restaurant experience also includes managing Toscana in Bryn Mawr, Pennsylvania. During his tenure at Sullivan&rsquo;s in Wilmington, Bill has enjoyed working with a number of charitable and professional groups. He is most proud of the restaurant team&rsquo;s work with the Ronald McDonald House of Delaware.</p>',NULL,'<p>Tim Baker has been with Sullivan&rsquo;s in Wilmington for four years. He was promoted to the executive chef position after spending a year as the sous chef. As a graduate of the Johnson &amp; Wales culinary program, Tim brings a wealth of both experience and expertise to his position.</p>',NULL),
	(30,3,'Atlanta','atlanta','In the heart of Buckhead - 3376 Peachtree Road','Atlanta','GA','30326','4045372828','4044185900','4044653723','','','dfgrille.atlanta@dfrg.com','dfgrille.atlanta@dfrg.com, dfgatlanta@dfrg.com, DFGAtlantaPD@dfrg.com',33.851135,-84.361389,'<p>Located in Atlanta?&rsquo;s bustling Buckhead neighborhood, Del Frisco&rsquo;?s Grille offers guests a stylish and inviting destination on one of the city?&rsquo;?s most vibrant thoroughfares, Peachtree Road. Within walking distance to luxury shopping at Lenox Square Mall and Phipps Plaza, the Grille is situated among the trend makers of Atlanta. Unlike any other American grill, Del Frisco&rsquo;?s Grille boasts Atlanta\'s only double-decker patio, which has become a standout feature and focal point of the ?Buckhead curve.? Here, guests are able to dine overlooking the energetic neighborhood.</p>','Buddy Smith','Kenny Perlman','AJ Buchanio','','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Del-Friscos-Grille/195364257252878','https://twitter.com/DFGrille','','88822','8706','https://www.google.com/maps/place/Del+Frisco\'s+Grille/@33.848949,-84.3663986,19z/data=!4m7!1m4!3m3!1s0x88f50f59d0e4d543:0xb06d1d7dbd776744!2s3376+Peachtree+Rd+NE,+Atlanta,+GA+30326!3b1!3m1!1s0x0:0x9dbe185b85b17165','published','http://media.dfrg.com/_delfriscosgrille/modal/dfg-LocationMap-atlanta.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_delfriscosgrille/locations/LocationMap-atlanta.png','http://media.dfrg.com/104425v2GrilleGroupDiningMenusProof-Atlanta.pdf','Buddy Smith fell in love with wine in 1994 when a sommelier sold him a bottle of 86 Grgich Hills Cab. He worked at Anthonys Fine Dining, a heritage Atlanta restaurant, as a banquet captain and banquet director. Next, Buddy moved to The Capital Grille and spent eight years under the tutelage of a master sommelier.  While there, he worked his way through the sommelier certification process while opening restaurants around the country and training servers. Buddy is excited to bring his knowledge and passion for wine to the family and guests of Del Friscos Grille in Atlanta.',NULL,'Kenny Perlman brings over 24 years of industry experience to his role as general manager of Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille. A native of Connecticut, Kenny began washing dishes in a neighborhood Italian deli at age 15. He eventually worked for a classic bar and grill, where he became close with the owners and was able to train and work in all stations the front of the house offered, eventually becoming manager. His work sparked a passion, and he pursued the restaurant industry with fervor, graduating from St. Leo University in 1998 with a degree in business administration with a specialization in hotel restaurant hospitality. He worked for Houston&rsquo;s as senior service manager for six years. From 2004 to 2009, he served as managing partner at Seasons 52. He was director of operations of Second Growth LLC from 2009 to 2011 and most recently was general manager at the flagship Stoney River located in Duluth before joining Del Frisco&rsquo;s Restaurant Group.',NULL,'Executive Chef AJ Buchanio of Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille in Atlanta brings a diverse background to the Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille team that stems from more than 17 years in the restaurant and hospitality industry. AJ is inspired as a chef by local ingredients that he incorporates into his creative menu and presentations. An Orlando native, AJ was drawn to the hospitality industry at a young age. Following graduation, he held various culinary positions including chef de cuisine at Evergreen Lodge in Yosemite, California. In 2009, AJ worked as the assistant maître d&rsquo; at Basin Harbor Club, in Vergennes, Vermount. In September 2011, AJ joined Del Frisco&rsquo;s Restaurant Group at Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse in Raleigh, North Carolina before moving to Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille in Atlanta.',NULL),
	(31,3,'Dallas','dallas','In the heart of Uptown Dallas  -  3232 McKinney Ave','Dallas','TX','75204','9728076152','9722327812','9723012014','','','dfgrille.dallas@dfrg.com','dfgrille.dallas@dfrg.com, dfgdallas@dfrg.com, DFGDallasPD@dfrg.com',32.803497,-96.799095,'<p>Del Frisco&rsquo;?s Grille is set in vibrant Uptown Dallas, the heart of Dallas? dining and social scene, just blocks from downtown. Our restaurant blends industrial and plush elements to create a stylish, social and relaxed atmosphere. Two energetic bars create a buzz throughout the restaurant unlike any other American grill, and floor-to-ceiling windows set the stage for an exciting dining experience. The patios provide the perfect glimpse of the action on the McKinney Avenue corridor and offer some of the best al fresco dining in Dallas. It?s a perfect place to meat up, drink up and soak in the atmosphere. Grab a seat and indulge in bold flavors in Big D.</p>\n<p>PARKING &amp; VALET: Complimentary valet is available during lunch, or you can park for free in the parking garage directly behind the Grille on Hall St. Simply ask a hostess for a parking token after dining with us. In the evenings, valet is $5.</p>','','Dominick Delledera','Antonio Zamora','','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Del-Friscos-Grille/195364257252878','https://twitter.com/DFGrille','','75061','8702','https://maps.google.com/maps?q=3232+McKinney+Avenue,+Suite+175,+Dallas,+TX+75204&hl=en&sll=32.94703,-96.819077&sspn=0.469613,0.672913&vpsrc=0&gl=us&hnear=3232+McKinney+Ave+#175,+Dallas,+Texas+75204&t=m&z=16','published','http://media.dfrg.com/_delfriscosgrille/modal/dfg-LocationMap-dallas.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_delfriscosgrille/locations/LocationMap-dallas.png','http://media.dfrg.com/104411v5GrilleGroupDiningMenusProof-Dallas.pdf','',NULL,'<p>Dominick Delledera is the general manager of Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille in Dallas and is a veteran of the restaurant industry. Dominick has always had a passion for the hospitality industry, taking after his father, who was a chef for more than 35 years. Delledera joined the Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille team with an extensive restaurant management background. Most recently, Dominick spent seven years with Seasons 52. In addition to Seasons 52, Delledera boasts more than 17 years of hospitality experience with Rothmann&rsquo;s Steakhouse in New York City, The Inn at Great Neck, Long Island, the Casa Monica Hotel and The Club at Hammock Beach in Florida.</p>',NULL,'',NULL),
	(32,3,'New York','new-york','Midtown Manhattan at Rockefeller Center - 50 Rockefeller Plaza','New York','NY','10020','2127670371','6463963303','6463963316','','','dfgrille.newyork@dfrg.com','dfgrille.newyork@dfrg.com, dfgnewyork@dfrg.com, DFGNewYorkCityPD@dfrg.com',40.759384,-73.978249,'<p>Del Frisco&rsquo;?s Grille in New York is located in the heart of Rockefeller Center at 50 Rockefeller Plaza near Radio City Music Hall, mere blocks from Times Square and Del Frisco&rsquo;?s Double Eagle Steak House. This unique American grill features a sweeping bar with a wood-burning oven, expansive walls showcasing over 700 bottles of wine and a sprawling patio perfect for al fresco city dining. The modern yet inviting decor is accented with stylish architectural elements and original works of art. Our bar buzzes with the energy of the after-work scene while the dining room provides the perfect setting for guests looking to escape from the rush of the city, meet with a client for a business lunch, or dine with friends and family.</p>','Kristin Mauritz','Nick D\'Ambrosio','Greg Lombardi','','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Del-Friscos-Grille/195364257252878','https://twitter.com/DFGrille','','67849','8701','https://maps.google.com/maps?q=del+friscos+grille+new+york&hl=en&ll=40.759383,-73.978243&spn=0.027273,0.042057&fb=1&gl=us&hq=del+friscos+grille&hnear=New+York&sqi=2&t=m&vpsrc=6&z=15&iwloc=A','published','http://media.dfrg.com/_delfriscosgrille/modal/dfg-LocationMap-newyork.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_delfriscosgrille/locations/LocationMap-newyork.png','http://media.dfrg.com/104444v2GrilleGroupDiningMenusProof-NewYork.pdf','<p>Kristin Mauritz, sommelier at Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille New York, began working at Del Frisco&rsquo;s Double Eagle Steak House in 2005. In 2007, her passion for wine grew from a hobby to a position as part-time sommelier for Del Frisco&rsquo;s Double Eagle Steak House in New York.&nbsp;Kristin opened the inaugural Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille in Rockefeller Center.</p>',NULL,'<p>Nick D&rsquo;Ambrosio is the general manager of Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille in New York, located in the heart of Midtown at Rockefeller Center. He began his career as a dishwasher at a small hometown restaurant in Northern New Jersey and quickly rose through the ranks in the back of the house to sous chef within two years. After honing his skills in the kitchen, Nick advanced to the front of the house, working every position from busser to manager, eventually becoming general manager. From there, he had the unique opportunity to become a partner in his own restaurant called Connie&rsquo;s Cafe in Hewitt, New Jersey from 1996 to 1999. After selling his stake, he moved to New York City and worked for the Smith &amp; Wollensky Restaurant. Nick went on to work at B.R. Guest from 2007 to 2011. Nick sits on the board of Station 7, a local charity helping children battle childhood cancer, and has been an active firefighter in his community for over 17 years.</p>',NULL,'',NULL),
	(33,3,'Phoenix','phoenix','2425 E. Camelback Road Suite #110','Phoenix','AZ','85016','6024662890','6023863224','6023863247','','','dfgrille.phoenix@dfrg.com','dfgphoenix@dfrg.com, DFGPhoenixPD@dfrg.com',33.509132,-112.028305,'<p>Del Frisco&rsquo;?s Grille in Phoenix is located in the center of Phoenix?&rsquo;s Camelback Corridor, the premier business and retail district. This unique American grill is just steps away from scenic Piestewa Peak, the historic Arizona Biltmore Resort and the star-studded Ritz-Carlton tower. The menu offers a wide variety of plates to savor or share with friends. Upstairs, the expansive Summit Bar offers al fresco dining and breathtaking views of the Valley and the Arizona sunset. A fashionable entrance and exit is easy with the Grille?s complimentary valet service.</p>\n<p>VALET: Complimentary valet available.</p>','Sarah Falconer','','Monte Healey','Sonya Delaney','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Del-Friscos-Grille/195364257252878','https://twitter.com/DFGrille','','88810','8703','https://maps.google.com/maps?f=q&source=s_q&hl=en&geocode;=&q=2425+E.+Camelback+Road+Suite+110+Phoenix,+AZ+85016&aq;=&sll=32.803496,-96.799095&sspn=0.013509,0.016029&vpsrc=0&ie=UTF8&hq;=&hnear=2425+E+Camelback+Rd,+Phoenix,+Arizona+85016&t=m&z=17&iwloc=A','published','http://media.dfrg.com/_delfriscosgrille/modal/dfg-LocationMap-phoenix.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_delfriscosgrille/locations/LocationMap-phoenix.png','http://media.dfrg.com/104445v2GrilleGroupDiningMenusProof-Phoenix.pdf','<p>Sarah Falconer has been in the hospitality industry for close to 20 years. Starting as a server, she worked her way through college in Durango, Colorado. With an anthropology degree in hand, she moved to Las Vegas. Always enjoying learning about wine, but still in a server/bartender position, Sarah became a sommelier with Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille in Las Vegas.</p>',NULL,'',NULL,'<p>Executive Chef Monte Healey began his culinary career at the age of 15 in Los Angeles. Master Chef Josie Le Balch provided Monte with his foundation in the culinary arts. From 1998 to 2005, Monte worked as both a front of house and back of house manager. Monte was excited for the opportunity to join the Del Frisco&rsquo;s family and be a leader in their future growth.</p>',NULL),
	(34,3,'Washington','washington-dc','1201 Pennsylvania Avenue, NW','Washington','DC','20004','2024504686','2023502215','2023502223','','','dfgrille.dc@dfrg.com','dfgrille.dc@dfrg.com, dfgdc@dfrg.com, DFGDCPD@dfrg.com',38.895355,-77.028282,'<p>Del Frisco\'s Grille in D.C. is buzzing with excitement in the heart of the nation?&rsquo;s capital between the U.S. Capitol and the White House on Pennsylvania Avenue. This one-of-a-kind American grill sits along wide, tree-lined sidewalks that brim with the energy of locals who live and work in the neighborhood as well as visitors from all over the globe. The interior features a 5,000-bottle wine wall, raw metal fixtures and lighting elements designed to mimic D.C. avenues and traffic circles. Pull up a seat outside at the 100-seat patio. The menu offers a wide variety of selections to savor or share with friends.</p>','Mary Phalen','Andrew Ojeda ','Brent Sick ','Fazlin Miller ','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Del-Friscos-Grille/195364257252878','https://twitter.com/DFGrille','','88816','8704','https://maps.google.com/maps?f=q&source=s_q&hl=en&geocode;=&q=1201+Pennsylvania+Avenue+NW+Washington,+DC++20004&aq;=&sll=33.509131,-112.028306&sspn=0.0067,0.008014&vpsrc=0&ie=UTF8&hq;=&hnear=1201+Pennsylvania+Ave+NW,+Washington,+District+of+Columbia+20004','published','http://media.dfrg.com/_delfriscosgrille/modal/dfg-LocationMap-dc.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_delfriscosgrille/locations/LocationMap-dc.png','http://media.dfrg.com/104424v2GrilleGroupDiningMenu-DC.pdf','<p>Mary Phalen was born and raised in Chicago and became interested in the foodservice industry while working to put herself through school. She attended California State University where she received her undergraduate degree in biology. After returning to the Chicago area in 1986, she attended The School of the Art Institute of Chicago, where she received a master&rsquo;s in fine art. Mary first became interested in fine wine service when she began a 15-year career with The Capital Grille steakhouse. Today, she is continuing her education and passion for fine wines with Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille here in D.C.</p>',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL),
	(35,1,'Chicago','chicago','58 E. Oak St.','Chicago','IL','60611','3128882499','3124487610','3124487660','','','delfriscos.chicago@dfrg.com','delfriscos.chicago@dfrg.com, dfchicago@dfrg.com, vxayavong@dfrg.com, DFChicagoPD@dfrg.com',41.900845,-87.626343,'<div itemscope itemtype=\"http://schema.org/VideoObject\">\n<h2 style=\"display:none;\">Video: <span itemprop=\"name\">Del Frisco&rsquo;s Double Eagle Steakhouse Chicago, IL</span></h2>\n<p><meta itemprop=\"thumbnailURL\" content=\"http://media.dfrg.com/del-friscos-video-thumbnail.png\" /><br />\n<meta itemprop=\"embedURL\" content=\"http:// www.youtube.com/embed/hRKSA3srmV0\" /><br />\n<iframe width=\"420\" height=\"315\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/hRKSA3srmV0\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"\"></iframe> <br />\n<meta itemprop=\"description\" content=\"Located in the heart of Chicago&rsquo;s Gold Coast neighborhood, Del Frisco&rsquo;s Double Eagle Steakhouse occupies three floors of the former Esquire Theater featuring stunning interiors and impeccable cuisine.\" />\n</div>\n<p>Del Frisco&rsquo;?s in Chicago occupies three floors of the historic Esquire Theater in the heart of the vibrant Gold Coast district. Located near high-end shopping, its lavish interior was designed to preserve the landmark theater?s historic architectural elements and create an intimate dining environment featuring a magnificent three-story wine tower. The experience is unlike any other steakhouse in Chicago. Guests can choose from a variety of spaces and ample options for private or semiprivate events.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Parking: Valet</li>\n<li>Features: Private rooms, view, bar, patio/outdoor seating, wine list of over 1,200 selections, wheelchair access</li>\n<li>Dress: Business casual</li>\n<li>Nonsmoking</li>\n<li>Payments: Cash, American Express, Discover, MasterCard, Visa and Diners Club</li>\n</ul>','Michael Taylor','Troy Smith','Jim Teutemacher','Anna Saavedra','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Del-Friscos-Double-Eagle-Steak-House/431080266915804','https://twitter.com/Del_Friscos','','88825','8650','https://maps.google.com/maps?q=58+E.+Oak+St.+Chicago+,+Illinois+-+60611&hl=en&sll=39.60871,-104.891039&sspn=0.013258,0.019269&hnear=58+E+Oak+St,+Chicago,+Illinois+60611&t=m&z=17','published','http://media.dfrg.com/_delfriscos/modal/df-LocationMap-chicago.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_delfriscos/locations/LocationMap-chicago.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_delfriscos/DF_PDmenu/DF_Chicago_PDmenu.pdf','Michael Taylor brings nearly 10 years of experience in the wine and restaurant industry to his role as wine director of Del Friscos Double Eagle Steak House in Chicago. Michael has served as an assistant sommelier and sommelier for several top restaurants managing extensive wine lists. Michael has earned his Level II certification from the Court of Master Sommeliers. He is excited to bring his passion and knowledge to Del Friscos in Chicago.',NULL,'With nearly 16 years of experience in the restaurant industry, Troy G. Smith brings extensive knowledge to his role as the general manager of Del Frisco&rsquo;s Double Eagle Steak House in Chicago. Troy started as a server at Del Frisco&rsquo;s Restaurant Group concept, Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse in Chicago, and in less than a year was promoted to assistant manager. Troy grew rapidly within the company, holding the manager position at Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse for four years. He was promoted to general manager of Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse in Naperville, which he held for five years until August 2012. While in Naperville, Troy learned to grow through community and charity involvement and the importance that both hold professionally and personally. In addition to this role, Troy continues to support community organizations and charitable causes that are important to him and the company.',NULL,'James A. Teutemacher brings 31 years of experience in the restaurant industry to his position as executive chef of Del Frisco&rsquo;s Double Eagle Steak House in Chicago. Jim always enjoyed cooking and being in the kitchen with his father. Recognizing his enthusiasm and passion, his father convinced a good friend, a local Greek diner owner, to give him the opportunity to work in the restaurant as a grill cook at the age of 14. He worked there for five years then trained under notable Executive Chef Steve Harney. From there, he has held executive chef positions at several elite steakhouses. Before joining Del Frisco&rsquo;s, Jim was the executive chef at Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse in Chicago for 13 years, a Del Frisco&rsquo;s Restaurant Group sister company.',NULL),
	(36,3,'Houston','houston','2800 Kirby Drive, Suite A-132','Houston','TX','77098','8326236168','8322660165','8322660464','','','dfgrille.houston@dfrg.com','dfgrille.houston@dfrg.com, dfghouston@dfrg.com, DFGHoustonPD@dfrg.com, pd8707@dfrg.com',29.741055,-95.418922,'<p>Del Frisco&rsquo;?s Grille is located in the vibrant River Oaks area, the heart of Houston&rsquo;??s dining and social scene. Industrial and lush elements create an atmosphere that is stylish, social and relaxed. Our energetic bar creates a buzz throughout the restaurant and sets the stage for an exciting dining experience that is unlike any other American grill. The patio provides the perfect perch to catch a glimpse of the action on the corner of Kirby and Westheimer and offers some of the best al fresco dining in Houston. It&rsquo;??s your place to eat with a friend and catch up on the latest or make new friends at the bar. Our food and drinks are built to share, so share the experience with your neighbors &ndash; they are just friends you haven&rsquo;??t met yet.</p>','Taylor Mundy ','Robert Campbell','Jeff Taylor','Amanda Friedman','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Del-Friscos-Grille/195364257252878','https://twitter.com/DFGrille','','103936','8707','https://maps.google.com/maps?client=safari&oe=UTF-8&q=2800+Kirby+Drive,+Suite+A-132,+Houston,+TX+77098&ie=UTF8&hq;=&hnear=2800+Kirby+Dr+#132,+Houston,+Harris,+Texas+77098&gl=us&t=m&ll=29.741054,-95.418921&spn=0.018631,','published','http://media.dfrg.com/_delfriscosgrille/modal/dfg-LocationMap-houston.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_delfriscosgrille/locations/LocationMap-houston.png','http://media.dfrg.com/104426v2GrilleGroupDiningMenusProof-Houston.pdf','',NULL,'<p>As general manager of Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille in Houston, Robert Campbell brings over 20 years of restaurant experience to lead a talented team and build long-term success for Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille. Robert began working as a server at a quick casual restaurant while attending college. Robert quickly developed a reputation as a &ldquo;fixer&rdquo; and was sent to the company&rsquo;s lowest-performing restaurants to identify areas of opportunity, resolve problems and implement structure. In 2008, after years of being on the road, Robert decided to settle down in Houston where he took a job at the newly opened Del Frisco&rsquo;s Double Eagle Steak House in the Galleria. Robert was soon promoted to management. His management skills coupled with his calm and warm demeanor are a perfect complement to the bustling and vibrant Grille scene.</p>',NULL,'<p>Executive Chef Jeff Taylor, of Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille in Houston has honed his talents and mastered his skills through his years with Del Frisco&rsquo;s Restaurant Group. His culinary style and taste is perfectly aligned with the Grille&rsquo;s menu &ndash; a modern take on the classic American bar and grill that draws inspiration from market-fresh ingredients. A graduate of Southeast Institute of Culinary Arts in St. Augustine, Florida, he started his career in Florida. After moving to Texas, he started his first position with Del Frisco&rsquo;s Restaurant Group and began work at Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse. There he thrived, finding Del Frisco&rsquo;s culture and style of service a perfect match for his talents. Taylor then moved to Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille and was promoted to a lead role. Taylor worked as a trainer for the opening of several Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille locations. Taylor is very involved with the Scouts and the Westlake Gators Swim Team in Katy, Texas.</p>',NULL),
	(37,3,'Santa Monica','santa-monica','1551 Ocean Ave.','Santa Monica','CA','90401','3103957333','3104641351','3105042723','','','dfgrille.santamonica@dfrg.com','dfgrille.santamonica@dfrg.com, DFGSantaMonicaPD@dfrg.com',34.012241,-118.495453,'<p>Del Frisco&rsquo;?s Grille, located on the northeast corner of Colorado and Ocean Avenue, offers diners the ultimate night out at a great location steps away from downtown. This exciting new American grill overlooks the iconic Santa Monica Pier. We dish up creative twists on American comfort classics. Modern, inviting, stylish and fun, the Grille takes the classic American bar and grill to new heights, drawing inspiration from bold flavors and local market-fresh ingredients. The energetic bar, a destination in itself, creates a buzz throughout the restaurant and sets the stage for an amazing night out. Del Frisco&rsquo;?s Grille is your place to Meat Up &amp; Drink Up.<br /><br /></p>\n<p>Valey Parking is $8 with validation adjacent to Del Frisco\'s Grille on Ocean Ave. Due to construction, Colorado Blvd. will be closed on and off. Please use alternate route via Broadway &amp; Ocean Ave.</p>','Adem Sash','Jeff Harrelson','Daniel Tiger','','https://www.facebook.com/DFGrilleSantaMonica','https://twitter.com/DFGrille','','108637','8709','https://maps.google.com/maps?q=1551+Ocean+Avenue,+Santa+Monica,+Los+Angeles,+California+90401&hl=en&ll=34.011831,-118.494737&spn=0.012202,0.022831&sll=29.741054,-95.418921&sspn=0.00639,0.011415&gl=us&geocode=Fa76BgId6Onv-A&hnear=1551+Ocean+Avenue&t=m&z=16','published','http://media.dfrg.com/_delfriscosgrille/modal/dfg-LocationMap-santamonica.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_delfriscosgrille/locations/LocationMap-santamonica.png','http://media.dfrg.com/104447v1GrilleGroupDiningMenusProof-SMonica1.pdf','With over 15 years of wine, mixology and beverage management, Sommelier Adem Sash oversees the wine program at Del Friscos Grille in Santa Monica, which boasts over 500 regional wines from California and across the globe.  Adem began his career with the Del Friscos Restaurant Group in 2000 at Del Friscos Double Eagle Steak House in New York City. His deep love for the culture of Del Friscos and his interest in wine and mixology continued to grow. Adem has also worked as a mixologist and as a sommelier at popular establishments in New York, Tokyo and the British Virgin Islands and is a standing Court of Masters Level II Sommelier, aggressively pursuing his Level III Sommelier certification.',NULL,'With over 20 years of experience in fine dining and hospitality, General Manager Jeffrey Harrelson is a seasoned operations and restaurant management professional. Jeffrey&rsquo;s debut in the food and beverage industry began with Hilton Hotels, and he quickly moved up the ranks as a restaurant and dining room manager for the company in both North Carolina and Florida. He has worked for an array of restaurant groups including Red Onion, Islands, PF Chang&rsquo;s and Fleming&rsquo;s Prime Steakhouse from Florida to Arizona and California. Jeffrey joined the esteemed Del Frisco&rsquo;s Restaurant Group team in spring 2013. Jeffrey is a graduate of East Carolina University with a degree in hotel and restaurant management.',NULL,'Executive Chef Daniel Tiger is seasoned in orchestrating custom menus. Daniel&rsquo;s love for cooking initially surfaced at a young age in the kitchen with his mother. After spending his high school years scouring library books for new cooking recipes, Daniel decided to enroll in Orange Coast Community College to study culinary arts. His career began at a small Orange County café, and over the years he honed his culinary skills working in an array of kitchens across Southern California. In 2008, he joined Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse, another Del Frisco&rsquo;s Restaurant Group concept. In 2011, Daniel relocated to Boston, where he served as sous chef for Del Frisco&rsquo;s Double Eagle Steak House. He finally returned to Southern California to join Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille as executive chef.',NULL),
	(38,3,'Palm Beach','palm-beach','340 Royal Poinciana Way, Suite 300','Palm Beach','FL','33480','5615572552','5612021573','5612036470','','','dfgrille.palmbeach@dfrg.com','dfgrille.palmbeach@dfrg.com, DFGPalmBeachPD@dfrg.com',26.718243,-80.041473,'<p>Located at the northeast corner of Royal Poinciana Plaza in the heart of Palm Beach,&nbsp;Del Frisco&rsquo;?s Grille combines a social atmosphere with exciting American grill cuisine, an expansive wine list and handcrafted cocktails. Del Frisco&rsquo;?s Grille has designed this location to integrate seamlessly with the island?s renowned lifestyle and culinary scene. Food and drinks are built to share, so get together with a friend or share the experience with your neighbor.&nbsp;We?&rsquo;re your place to Meat Up &amp; Drink Up.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>DIRECTIONS (Flagler Memorial Bridge is Closed):</strong></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>1. From Interstate 95, exit FL-704 E./ Okeechobee Blvd. toward downtown, drive about 1.7 miles.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>2. Drive through downtown, then go over the Royal Palm Bridge, about 0.5 miles.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>3. Turn left onto Cocoanut Row, about 0.7 miles.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>4. Turn left onto Royal Poinciana Plaza, Del Frisco\'s Grille is in the front of the plaza.</span></p>','Elissa Pablo','Alev Ersoy','Michael McLaurin','Danielle Houtman','https://www.facebook.com/DFGrillePalmBeach','https://twitter.com/DFGrille','','110761','8705','https://www.google.com/maps?q=340+Royal+Poinciana+Way,+Palm+Beach,+FL&hl=en&sll=32.834598,-96.771542&sspn=0.201642,0.41851&oq=340+Royal+Poin&hnear=340+Royal+Poinciana+Way,+Palm+Beach,+Florida+33480&t=m&z=17','published','http://media.dfrg.com/_delfriscosgrille/modal/dfg-LocationMap-palmbeach.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_delfriscosgrille/locations/LocationMap-palmbeach.png','http://media.dfrg.com/104446v3GrilleGroupDiningMenu-PalmBeach.pdf','<p>Elissa Pablo is Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille&rsquo;s sommelier and dining room manager. Originally from South Florida, Elissa has more than a dozen years of experience in restaurants. Her success comes from personally working in every position in the front of the house. Elissa&rsquo;s work includes educating servers on the wine options available at the restaurants. Her favorite wines are newer releases such as California Zinfandels. Elissa received her bachelor&rsquo;s degree in art history from Florida Atlantic University.</p>',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL),
	(39,3,'Fort Worth','fort-worth','154 East 3rd St.','Fort Worth','TX','76102','8178879900','8173809375','8173809589','','','dfgrille.fortworth@dfrg.com','dfgrille.fortworth@dfrg.com, DFGFortWorthPD@dfrg.com',32.755333,-97.331085,'<p>Now Open!</p>\n<p>Located in the heart of downtown Fort Worth, in the brand new Sundance Square Plaza, Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille is the perfect spot to enjoy a fantastic night in one Texas&rsquo; finest cities. Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille in Fort Worth is next to amazing entertainment and nightlife, including The Flying Saucer, the famed AMC Palace 9, and Bass Performance Hall, as well as luxury hotels like the Worthington Renaissance and Ashton Hotels. For an evening you and your friends won&rsquo;t soon forget, meat up and drink up at Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille in Fort Worth before moseying along to the next watering hole.</p>','','Kenneth Davis','','','https://www.facebook.com/DFGrilleFortWorth','https://twitter.com/DFGrille','','110764','8710','https://www.google.com/maps?q=154+East+3rd+St.,+Fort+Worth,+TX&hl=en&sll=26.71691,-80.042203&sspn=0.006699,0.013078&hnear=154+E+3rd+St,+Fort+Worth,+Texas+76102&t=m&z=17','published','http://media.dfrg.com/_delfriscosgrille/modal/dfg-LocationMap-fortworth.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_delfriscosgrille/locations/LocationMap-fortworth.png','http://media.dfrg.com/104427v3GrilleGroupDiningMenusProof-FortWorth.pdf','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL),
	(40,3,'Chestnut Hill','chestnut-hill','33 Boylston St. Suite 3370','Chestnut Hill','MA','02467','6176083682','','','','','dfgrille.chestnuthill@dfrg.com','dfgrille.chestnuthill@dfrg.com, DFGChestnutHill@dfrg.com',42.321896,-71.170258,'<p>Now open!</p>\n<p>Centrally located in the heart of Chestnut Hill just 15 minutes from The Shops at The Prudential Center &amp; The Burlington Mall, Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille is on Boston&rsquo;s famous Boylston St. just past Hammond St which is only minutes from the Chestnut Hill T Stop. Over looking Hammond Pond at the Chestnut Hill Shopping Center which has been transformed into the newly renamed <strong>The Street</strong>, our location is easy to get to from both the City and locations further north!</p>\n<p>We&rsquo;re your place to Meat Up &amp; Drink Up.</p>','Christina Norman ','Mike Tobins ','David Silva','Laura Elkman ','https://www.facebook.com/DFGrilleChestnutHill','https://twitter.com/DFGrilleCH','','114997','8708','https://www.google.com/maps?q=33+Boylston+St.+Suite+3370+Chestnut+Hill,+MA+02467&hl=en&sll=42.321996,-71.169917&sspn=0.007147,0.016512&hnear=33+Boylston+St+#3370,+Chestnut+Hill,+Massachusetts+02467&t=m&z=17','published','http://media.dfrg.com/_delfriscosgrille/modal/dfg-LocationMap-chestnuthill.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_delfriscosgrille/locations/LocationMap-default.png','http://media.dfrg.com/105138v1DFG-ChestnutHillGroupDiningDigital.pdf','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL),
	(41,3,'Southlake','southlake','1200 E. Southlake Blvd.','Southlake','TX','76092','8174103777','8173809609','8173809609','','','dfgrille.southlake@dfrg.com','dfgrille.southlake@dfrg.com, DFGSouthlake@dfrg.com',32.941132,-97.133583,'<p>Now Open!</p>\n<p>Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille in Southlake is located right in the middle of the shopping and nightlife of Southlake Town Square. You can spend the day shopping at popular stores and boutiques before meeting up with your friends for dinner and drinks or a show at the Harkins Theatre. Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille is located right off of Highway 114 on the northwest corner of Carroll Avenue and Southlake Boulevard. You can enjoy our luxurious dining room or one of our two outdoor patios to, \"meat up and drink up,\" with your friends old and new.</p>','','Sabrina Scully','Aaron Henschen','','https://www.facebook.com/DFGrilleSouthlake','https://twitter.com/DFGrilleSLake','','115000','8712','https://www.google.com/maps?q=1200+E+Southlake+Blvd,+Southlake,+TX&hl=en&sll=32.941128,-97.133577&sspn=0.008149,0.01442&oq=12&t=h&hnear=1200+E+Southlake+Blvd,+Southlake,+Texas+76092&z=17&iwloc=A','published','http://media.dfrg.com/_delfriscosgrille/modal/dfg-LocationMap-southlake.png','http://media.dfrg.com/_delfriscosgrille/locations/LocationMap-default.png','http://media.dfrg.com/105139v1GrilleGroupDiningMenuDigital-Southlake.pdf',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
