	(5,2,25,'Raising The \"Steaks\" - Sullivan\'s Steakhouse Unveils A Contemporary New Design ','','<p>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE:<br /><br />Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse in Palm Desert debuts a refreshed and youthful look after interior and exterior renovations</p>\n<p>PALM DESERT, Calif. (March 17, 2014) &ndash; Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse, a favorite Desert neighborhood restaurant known for its hand cut steaks, fresh seafood, and delectable side dishes, is pleased to debut the restaurant&rsquo;s highly anticipated new look, consisting of major renovations to the bar and lounge, main dining room, private dining rooms, patio, and more.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>With a contemporary vision, the refreshed design emphasizes a more vibrant color scheme and lighter atmosphere throughout the 7,200-square-foot establishment. Design elements bring more natural light into the restaurant, energizing it with a fresh new vibe. &nbsp;High-top stools surround a rustic communal dining table, adding depth and sparking conversation around the bar and lounge, which now boasts seating for 60 guests. &nbsp;Al fresco dining has been expanded for guests who want to soak up the sun and keep an eye on the scene along El Paseo. &nbsp;Sleek new awnings along the patio attract the &ldquo;in crowd.&rdquo;</p>\n<p>&ldquo;We are so excited to show off our new look to our loyal guests,&rdquo; said Keith Sansone, general manager of Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse. &nbsp;&ldquo;Sullivan&rsquo;s is a great place to wine and dine any night of the week, and our fresh new look reflects the personality and energy of our savvy guests.&rdquo;</p>\n<p>Guests will notice a difference immediately when they enter the restaurant, as walls have been removed to enlarge and brighten the foyer. &nbsp;Hand-crafted artwork includes pops of deep red and gold around the bar. &nbsp;Handsome dark woods and residential-inspired detailing juxtaposed with champagne accents and more contemporary, clean lines create a sexy atmosphere. &nbsp;The lounge has also been reconfigured with semi-private nooks and plush leather booths, perfect for intimate dates and private business meetings. &nbsp;</p>\n<p>The refreshed design is an extension of Sullivan&rsquo;s new approach, as the popular restaurant recently introduced a revved up menu, too. &nbsp;With Executive Chef Kevin Favinger at the helm, Sullivan&rsquo;s now has a new menu which features an abundance of seasonal produce, lighter fare, and succulent seafood. &nbsp;Bringing new energy to the restaurant, Chef Favinger is serving bright new dishes like Kale Salad with Gala Apples, Caramelized Cauliflower and Broiled Wild Salmon. &nbsp;Chef is also featuring a $39 three-course prix fixe menu called &ldquo;The Sure Thing,&rdquo; a lock for guests who like to sample a variety of Sullivan&rsquo;s much-loved classics: Cheesesteak Eggrolls, Crispy Shanghai Calamari and Filet Mignon.</p>\n<p>As always, the extensive wine list at Sullivan&rsquo;s boasts 400 selections &nbsp;from the top regions in the world, creating a stand-out choice for guests with discerning taste who want the best wines to complement their hand-cut steaks. &nbsp;Sullivan&rsquo;s signature martini, The Knockout, is made with sweet Hawaiian Gold pineapples which have been soaked in orange vodka and hand-squeezed into a cold and refreshing martini glass and is still the best way to kick off a memorable evening.</p>\n<p>Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse is located at 73-505 El Paseo #2600, Palm Desert, CA 92260. &nbsp;To learn more, please visit www.sullivanssteakhouse.com or call (760) 341-3560 for reservations and additional information.</p>\n<p>About Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse</p>\n<p>Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse, founded in 1996, is a favorite neighborhood restaurant. &nbsp;Known for its hand cut steaks, Sullivan&rsquo;s is equally well-known for its fresh seafood, delectable side dishes, mouth-watering desserts and award-winning wine list. &nbsp;Sullivan&rsquo;s is the perfect place to wine and dine any night of the week &ndash; with food, drinks, and live entertainment under one roof. &nbsp;Each Sullivan&rsquo;s features live music in the bar area nightly, delicious artisan cocktails, and exceptional food and wine.</p>\n<p>Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse is the sister restaurant to the renowned Del Frisco&rsquo;s Double Eagle Steak House and Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille, all of which are owned by Del Frisco&rsquo;s Restaurant Group (NASDAQ: DFRG) of Southlake, TX. &nbsp;There are 19 Sullivan&rsquo;s across the country, which also creates a seamless dining experience for savvy business travelers. &nbsp;Sullivan&rsquo;s retains its Southern roots, offering true Southern hospitality at each and every location. &nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','local','2014-03-17','published'),
	(6,3,42,'Del Frisco\'s Grille to Open June 14th in Burlington ','Del Frisco\'s Grille ','<p><em>Located on Middlesex Turnpike, Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille offers a creative twist on American comfort cuisine, local fare and an extensive wine list</em></p>\n<p>BURLINGTON, MA - (May 28, 2014) &mdash; Del Frisco&rsquo;s Restaurant Group, which launched Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille at The Street will debut their second Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille in Burlington, Massachusetts. Opening on June 14th, the Grille occupies 7,900 square feet of space right of off Middlesex Turnpike across from the popular Burlington Mall. &nbsp;A much anticipated addition to the area, Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille takes the traditional bar and grill to new heights, using bold flavors, regional ingredients and local flair in many of its dishes.</p>\n<p>Executive Chef Rob DiTonno, who has been with Del Frisco&rsquo;s Restaurant Group for the past three years at Del Frisco&rsquo;s Double Eagle Steakhouse in Boston&rsquo;s Liberty Wharf will feature local favorites like the Berkshire Pork Meatballs and East Coast Fish Tacos, alongside new Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille classics that are easy to share with friends: Wood Oven-Baked Flatbreads, Cheesesteak Egg Rolls, and Ahi Tuna Tacos. Three days a week the menu will feature the &ldquo;Daily Dish,&rdquo; a daily special served Tuesday, Wednesday and Thursday. The menu is rounded out with a selection of prime steaks, hearty salads, formidable sandwiches and chef-inspired entrees. Even late night revelers will get up early for a decadent brunch at the Grille that includes an out-of-this-world Red Velvet Belgian Waffle and Shredded Pork Burrito.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>With 300 selections showcased in the Grille&rsquo;s collection of glass wine displays, Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille offers a wide variety of choices that appeal to every palate from the adventurous to the traditional. &nbsp;Del Frisco&rsquo;s Director of Wine, David O&rsquo;Day, has carefully selected wines from established and up-and-coming regions in the world, creating an unparalleled and adventurous wine list, surprisingly more extensive than those found in a traditional bar and grill.</p>\n<p>&ldquo;Our loyal guests at Del Frisco&rsquo;s Double Eagle Steak House in Boston&rsquo;s Liberty Wharf and at Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille at The Street in Chestnut Hill have been so good to us,&rdquo; said Mark Mednansky, CEO of Del Frisco&rsquo;s Restaurant Group. &nbsp;&ldquo;We are excited to extend our warm, genuine hospitality to our friends in Burlington and welcome them to Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille. &nbsp;This is a modern American bar and grill and truly the best place in town to come in with friends for a great glass of wine and a steak or to unwind with a local beer and a delicious flatbread.&rdquo;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The Grille, open for lunch, dinner and brunch, offers two floors of dining with seating for 220 guests along with an upstairs bar with 10 seats, a downstairs bar with 20 seats and an outdoor patio with fireplace with seating for 100. A fun addition to local nightlife, the bar at Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille gets the party going with imaginative, memorable cocktails including The Morning After, The Kilt Lifter and Apt. 5D &ndash; plus six beers and two wines on tap.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&ldquo;We can&rsquo;t wait to show Burlington what Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille is all about. This is the perfect place to come for a business lunch, casual night out, post work drinks and dinner, or girls&rsquo; night out,&rdquo; said general manager Nick Foley, whose previous experience includes GM roles in the community. &ldquo;We&rsquo;ve created a space that is inviting, a menu that is truly delicious and an atmosphere that is downright fun.&rdquo;</p>\n<p>Designed by Boston-based architecture firm, Sousa Design Architects, the restaurant invites guests with a blend of strong and warm elements by combining dark wood with deep red upholstered seating and large oversized lights for comfort. An atmosphere that is simultaneously sophisticated and inviting, exposed structures, an open kitchen and beautiful LED lighting create a high-end sophisticated space that compliments the product.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille is located at 92 Middlesex Turnpike in Burlington, Massachusetts. The restaurant will serve lunch daily, Monday &ndash; Friday from 11 a.m. to 4 p.m. and dinner nightly, Monday &ndash; Friday 4 p.m. &ndash; 11 p.m.; Saturday, 3 p.m. &ndash; 11p.m. and Sunday 3 p.m. &ndash; 10- p.m.; Saturday and Sunday brunch 11 a.m. &ndash; 3 p.m.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>For more information, please visit Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille online at www.delfriscosgrille.com, or like us on Facebook at facebook.com/DFGrilleBurlington. <br /><br /><strong>About Del Frisco\'s Grille</strong></p>\n<p>Del Frisco\'s Grille is modern, inviting, stylish and fun. Taking the classic bar and grill to new heights, Del Frisco\'s Grille draws inspiration from bold flavors and market-fresh ingredients. The energetic bar, a destination in itself, creates a buzz throughout the restaurant and sets the stage for an amazing night out. &nbsp; There are 11 Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grilles across the country. &nbsp;It is the proud winner of the 2012 Hot Concepts Award presented annually by Nation&rsquo;s Restaurant News. Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille in Manhattan also won the 2012 Concierge Choice Award for Casual Dining, an award given by the NYC Association of Hotel Concierges to honor those who create exceptional experiences for New York City visitors.</p>\n<p>About Del Frisco\'s Restaurant Group</p>\n<p>Del Frisco\'s Grille is owned by Del Frisco\'s Restaurant Group (NASDAQ: DFRG). &nbsp;Based in Southlake, Texas, near Dallas, Del Frisco\'s Restaurant Group is a collection of more than 30 restaurants located across the country, including Del Frisco\'s Grille, Del Frisco\'s Double Eagle Steak House, and Sullivan\'s Steakhouse. &nbsp;Del Frisco\'s Double Eagle Steak House serves up flawless cuisine that\'s bold and delicious, an extensive award-winning wine list and a level of service that reminds guests that they\'re the boss. &nbsp;Sullivan\'s Steakhouse is the perfect place to wine and dine any night of the week - with outstanding food, hand-shaken martinis, an award winning wine list, and live entertainment all under one roof. &nbsp;All of the restaurants create a seamless dining experience for savvy business and leisure travelers who regularly dine or entertain away from home.</p>\n<p><em>CONTACT: Meghan Almquist</em><br /><em>CM Communications</em><br /><em>malmquist@cmcommunications.com</em><br /><em>617-536-3400</em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','local','2014-05-28','published'),
	(7,2,NULL,'Summer Fling Launches at Sullivan\'s Steakhouses','Del Frisco\'s Restaurant Group ','<p class=\"MsoNormal\"  left;\"><em><span  11.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Calibri\',\'sans-serif\';\">DEL FRISCO&rsquo;S RESTAURANT GROUP LAUNCHES &ldquo;SUMMER FLING&rdquo; AT SULLIVAN&rsquo;S STEAKHOUSES<br /><br /></span></em><span  150%;\">(SOUTHLAKE, Texas) June 2, 2014 &ndash; Thomas Dritsas, vice president and corporate executive chef for Del Frisco&rsquo;s Restaurant Group, is pleased to announce that the company is tempting guests with a Summer Fling &ndash; a Six-Ounce Filet Mignon and Half Live Maine Lobster &ndash; featured through Labor Day on the &ldquo;Sullivan&rsquo;s Seasonals&rdquo; menu at all 19 Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouses across the country.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"  150%; text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"  150%; text-align: left;\"><span  150%;\">&ldquo;It&rsquo;s time to celebrate summer at Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse,&rdquo; said Thomas Dritsas, vice president and corporate executive chef for Del Frisco&rsquo;s Restaurant Group.</span><span  150%;\">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span  150%;\">&ldquo;Our Summer Fling is one guests will always remember &ndash; and our seasonal menu is loaded with the freshest ingredients that capture the intensity of the season.&rdquo;</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"  150%; text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"  150%; text-align: left;\"><span  150%;\">The Summer Fling is the newest offering on the Sullivan&rsquo;s Seasonals menu.</span><span  150%;\">&nbsp; </span><span  150%;\">Offered for just $42 for a limited time from now until September 1, the Summer Fling is a Six-Ounce Filet Mignon broiled to perfection and paired with Half Live Maine Lobster, making Sullivan&rsquo;s the perfect place to wine and dine any night of the week.</span><span  150%;\">&nbsp; </span><span  150%;\">The other stars of the Sullivan&rsquo;s Seasonals menu include the Lobster Tail Trio for just $44, featuring fresh, succulent lobster tails prepared three ways.</span><span  150%;\">&nbsp; </span><span  150%;\">Each lobster tail is three-and-half-ounces.</span><span  150%;\">&nbsp; </span><span  150%;\">One is simply broiled and served with lemon and butter, one is served Scampi style with rich buerre blanc and diced tomatoes and the third is fried Tempura style and drizzled with honey mustard.</span><span  150%;\">&nbsp; </span><span  150%;\">The tantalizing threesome is served with Sullivan&rsquo;s decadent Garlic Horseradish Mashed Potatoes.</span><span  150%;\">&nbsp; </span><span  150%;\">Heirloom Tomatoes are at their best during summer, and Sullivan&rsquo;s features a classic presentation with Buffalo Mozzarella, Basil Pesto and Aged Balsamic Vinegar.</span><span  150%;\">&nbsp; </span><span  150%;\">The perfect finish to a summer dinner is Sullivan&rsquo;s refreshing Key Lime Pie.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"  150%; text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"  150%; text-align: left;\"><strong><span  11.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Calibri\',\'sans-serif\';\">About Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse</span></strong></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"  left;\"><span  11.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Calibri\',\'sans-serif\';\">Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse, founded in 1996, is a favorite neighborhood restaurant.&nbsp; Known for its hand cut steaks, Sullivan&rsquo;s is equally well-known for its fresh seafood, delectable side dishes, mouth-watering desserts and award-winning wine list.&nbsp; Sullivan&rsquo;s is the perfect place to wine and dine any night of the week &ndash; with food, drinks, and live entertainment under one roof.&nbsp; Each Sullivan&rsquo;s features live music in the bar area nightly, delicious artisan cocktails, and exceptional food and wine.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"  left;\"><span  Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt;\">Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse is the sister restaurant to the renowned Del Frisco&rsquo;s Double Eagle Steak House and Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille, all of which are owned by Del Frisco&rsquo;s Restaurant Group (NASDAQ: DFRG) of Southlake, TX.</span><span  Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt;\">&nbsp; </span><span  Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt;\">There are 19 Sullivan&rsquo;s across the country, which creates a seamless dining experience for savvy travelers.</span><span  Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt;\">&nbsp; </span><span  Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt;\">Sullivan&rsquo;s retains its Southern roots, offering true Southern hospitality at each and every location.</span><span  Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt;\">&nbsp; </span><span  Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt;\">Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse can be found online at </span><a   href=\"http://www.sullivanssteakhouse.com/\">www.sullivanssteakhouse.com</a></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"  left;\" align=\"center\"><strong><span  11.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Calibri\',\'sans-serif\';\">Media contact:</span></strong><span  11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">&nbsp; Casey Shaughnessy, Glodow Nead Communications, 415-394-6500, ext. 212.</span></p>','national','2014-06-02','published'),
	(8,3,NULL,'Del Frisco\'s Grille Introduces Triple Treat','Del Frisco\'s Restaurant Group ','<p><strong>Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille Introduces Triple Treat&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p><em>Spiked Milkshake + Sumptuous Burger + Classic Frites = &ldquo;Happier&rdquo; Version of an American Classic</em></p>\n<p>SOUTHLAKE, TX (June 3, 2014) &ndash; This summer, Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille is adding the new Triple Treat to its menu &ndash; an adult milkshake, opulent double patty burger and classic frites. Resembling a certain childhood favorite, this adult version of a classic combo meal will leave guests more than happy.</p>\n<p>The Triple Treat features the Grille&rsquo;s Prime Cheeseburger &ndash; two flavorful patties made of a mouthwatering blend of USDA Prime short rib, brisket and chuck topped with cheese, lettuce, tomato, pickles and sloppy sauce between a brioche bun. No burger meal would be complete without a fry component; Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille gives guests the choice of Original, Sea Salt and Parmesan or Sweet Potato Frites. The grand finale is the Adult Milkshake &ndash; named not only for its 21-and-over ingredients, but also for a level of decadence that the most mature of palates will appreciate: Nocello Walnut Liqueur, Cr&egrave;me de Cacao Chocolate Liqueur and vanilla ice cream.</p>\n<p>&ldquo;American comfort classics are our wheelhouse, but we never miss an opportunity to add a fun and modern twist to familiar pairings with exceptional ingredients,&rdquo; said Thomas Dristas, vice president and corporate executive chef of Del Frisco\'s Restaurant Group.</p>\n<p>Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille is committed to using ingredients of the upmost quality. While known for its superb quality of meat, serving USDA prime only, the Grille&rsquo;s adult milkshake now shares the indulgent spotlight.</p>\n<p>&ldquo;In a fast food nation, it is rare to find this old-time staple that isn&rsquo;t frozen, fried and thrown through a drive-thru window,&rdquo; explains Mark S. Mednansky, CEO of Del Frisco&rsquo;s Restaurant Group. &ldquo;The Triple Treat takes us back to being a kid and grabbing a bite with friends and family &ndash; but we\'ve kicked it up with our must-have adult milkshake worth sacrificing the toy for.&rdquo;</p>\n<p>Guests can enjoy this mouthwatering American staple, available June through August at Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille&rsquo;s 12 locations nationwide.</p>\n<p>###</p>\n<p><strong>About Del Frisco\'s Grille</strong></p>\n<p>Del Frisco\'s Grille is modern, inviting, stylish and fun. Taking the classic bar and grill to new heights, Del Frisco\'s Grille draws inspiration from bold flavors and market-fresh ingredients. The energetic bar, a destination in itself, creates a buzz throughout the restaurant and sets the stage for an amazing night out. &nbsp;There are 11 Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grilles across the country with the 12th location set to open June 14, 2014 in Burlington, Massachusetts. &nbsp;It is the proud winner of the 2012 Hot Concepts Award presented annually by Nation&rsquo;s Restaurant News.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>About Del Frisco\'s Restaurant Group, Inc.</p>\n<p>Based in Southlake, Texas, near Dallas, Del Frisco\'s Restaurant Group, Inc. (NASDAQ: DFRG) is a collection of 40 restaurants across 20 states and Washington, D.C., including Del Frisco\'s Double Eagle Steak House, Sullivan\'s Steakhouse, and Del Frisco\'s Grille. Del Frisco\'s Double Eagle Steak House serves up flawless cuisine that\'s bold and delicious, an extensive award-winning wine list and a level of service that reminds guests that they\'re the boss. Sullivan\'s Steakhouse is a great neighborhood place for a big night out on the town - with outstanding food, hand-shaken martinis, an award winning wine list, and live entertainment all under one roof. Del Frisco\'s Grille is modern, inviting, stylish and fun, taking the classic bar and grill to new heights, and drawing inspiration from bold flavors and market-fresh ingredients.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','national','2014-06-03','published'),
	(10,3,36,'Del Frisco\'s Grille Named Among the Nation\'s Hottest Restaurants','Stevens Group ','<p><strong>Houston and Fort Worth locations both included on OpenTable&rsquo;s 2014 list</strong></p>\n<p>HOUSTON, TX March 20, 2014 &mdash; Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille has been named among the &ldquo;100 Hottest Restaurants in the U.S.&rdquo; by OpenTable, a popular online real-time restaurant reservation service. Both of Del Frisco&rsquo;s eateries in Houston and Fort Worth made the top 100 cut, and no other restaurant in Houston or Fort Worth was named among the hottest. The top 100 was based on OpenTable&rsquo;s survey of more than 5 million diners who ranked approximately 19,000 American popular restaurants in 21 states.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&ldquo;The people have spoken,&rdquo; said regional manager Arthur Mooradian. &ldquo;This list reflects what is hot across the country, and Del Frisco&rsquo;s is honored to be included. We pride ourselves on providing guests with great ambiance, fantastic food and stellar cocktails, and we offer them a big thanks to them for giving us the thumbs up.&rdquo;</p>\n<p>Del Frisco&rsquo;s locations in Houston and Fort Worth offer patrons a memorable dining experience of impeccable chef-driven cuisine, an extensive wine list and cocktail menu, and unparalleled hospitality in an energetic atmosphere.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille in Houston is located at 2800 Kirby, Houston, TX 77098. &nbsp;</p>\n<p>For reservations, please call (713) 961-0333</p>\n<p># # #</p>\n<p><strong>About Del Frisco\'s Grille</strong></p>\n<p>Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille is modern, inviting, stylish and fun. Taking the classic bar and grill to new heights, Del Frisco\'s Grille draws inspiration from bold flavors and market-fresh ingredients. It is the proud winner of the &ldquo;2012 Hot Concepts Award&rdquo; presented annually by Nation&rsquo;s Restaurant News. Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille is the sister restaurant to the renowned Del Frisco&rsquo;s Double Eagle Steak House and Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse, both owned by Del Frisco&rsquo;s Restaurant Group (NASDAQ: DFRG) of Southlake, TX. For more information on Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille, please visit http://delfriscosgrille.com/.</p>\n<p>MEDIA CONTACT: Jessica Meyerson, Stevens Group, 949.278.2759, Jessica@stevensprgroup.com</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','local','2014-03-20','published'),
	(11,3,37,'Del Frisco\'s Grille Santa Monica Announces Monthly Wine Events by One of LA\'s Top Sommeliers, Adem Sash ','Spin Public Relations','<p><strong>PlumpJack Wine Dinner on Wednesday, March 19 and the Launch of Sommelier Saturdays on March 29</strong></p>\n<p>LOS ANGELES (March 4, 2014) &ndash;Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille Santa Monica announces two new wine-focused events in March hosted by their talented Sommelier, Adem Sash. The first is a PlumpJack wine dinner on Wednesday, March 19, followed by the launch of Sommelier Saturdays wine lessons on Saturday, March 29, and continuing the last Saturday of every month. Adem will share his knowledge from 15 years in wine, mixology and beverage management, and from his current role as the head of Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille&rsquo;s wine program, which boasts more than 500 regional wines from California.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>To kick off the monthly events, Adem will host a wine dinner featuring PlumpJack Wines on March 19 at 7:00 p.m., which will feature a selection of the winery&rsquo;s finest, accompanied by a four-course menu from Executive Chef Daniel Tiger for $175. The menu will feature items such as Grilled Baby Octopus, Cherry Cab braised Wild Boar Belly, Filet Mignon and a Syrah Sorbet with Wild Berries from the Farmers&rsquo; Market. PlumpJack Winery is located in the heart of the renowned Oakville region of Napa Valley, and is highly regarded for the quality of its Cabernet Sauvignon. Adem, along with knowledgeable PlumpJack representative, will educate guests about the wine selection and recommend some enticing food and wine pairings available at Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille.</p>\n<p>Starting on Saturday, March 29, Adem will launch a monthly wine series called Sommelier Saturdays, which invites wine lovers for an intimate, two-hour wine lesson along with hors d&rsquo;oeuvres for $35 per person. Starting at 1 p.m., guests will learn about wine from one of the city&rsquo;s top sommeliers about topics such as, the differences between Pinot Noirs from different regions, oaked vs. unoaked Chardonnay and the art of sounding savvy when speaking with a restaurant&rsquo;s sommelier. Sommelier Saturdays will be held on the last Saturday of every month.</p>\n<p>Limited space is available. Reservations can be made by calling: (310) 395-7333. Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille Santa Monica is located at 1551 Ocean Ave., on the corner of Ocean Ave. and Colorado Blvd, and valet parking is available adjacent to restaurant.</p>\n<p><strong>ABOUT ADEM SASH:</strong></p>\n<p>With over 15 years of wine, mixology, and beverage management, Adem Sash oversees the wine program at Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille Santa Monica. Adem has an extensive background in the beverage field and a reputation for professionalism, initiative, and creativity.</p>\n<p>Adem began with the Del Frisco&rsquo;s Restaurant Group in 2000, while pursuing his master&rsquo;s degree in Criminal Forensic Psychology from John Jay College of Criminal Justice, at Del Frisco&rsquo;s Double Eagle Steakhouse in the heart of New York City. Following graduation, his deep love for the culture of Del Frisco&rsquo;s and his interest in wine and mixology continued to grow.</p>\n<p>Adem has also worked as a mixologist and as a sommelier at popular establishments in New York, Tokyo, and the British Virgin Islands. Adem provides passionate and professional service to high-end clientele and has become a proven leader in wine/food pairing, mixology and beverage management that wholly defines success in the beverage industry today. He is a standing Court of Masters Level II Sommelier, and is aggressively pursuing his Level III Sommelier certification.</p>\n<p><strong>ABOUT DEL FRISCO&rsquo;S GRILLE SANTA MONICA:</strong></p>\n<p>Del Frisco\'s Grille is an exciting eatery located adjacent from the Santa Monica Pier, that combines the atmosphere of an American bar &amp; grill with upscale entrees, an extensive wine list &amp; hand-crafted cocktails. &nbsp;This Santa Monica location is the first for the company in California and the seventh location in the country. &nbsp;Taking the classic bar and grill to new heights, Del Frisco\'s Grille draws inspiration from bold flavors and market-fresh ingredients. The energetic bar, a destination in itself, creates a buzz throughout the restaurant and sets the stage for an amazing night out. &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\n<p>Located 1551 Ocean Avenue, on the corner of Ocean Avenue and Colorado Boulevard, Del Frisco\'s Grille is open Monday- Saturday from 11:00 a.m. to 11:00 p.m. and Sunday from 11:00 a.m. to 10:00 p.m. The bar is open late. Brunch is served Saturday and Sunday. For more information visit http://delfriscosgrille.com/menu/santa-monica/.</p>\n<p><strong>ABOUT PLUMPJACK WINES:</strong></p>\n<p>In 1992, Gordon Getty and Gavin Newsom founded San Francisco\'s popular PlumpJack Wines on Fillmore Street on the principle of offering helpful information in a friendly, non-intimidating manner to transform the wine purchasing experience into one of fun and discovery.</p>\n<p>Since then, The PlumpJack Group portfolio has expanded to include a diverse collection of hospitality and lifestyle businesses including luxury resorts, award-winning wineries, popular restaurants and nightlife establishments, catering and retail establishments, as well as the PlumpJack Development Company. PlumpJack Winery sits squarely in the heart of Napa Valley&rsquo;s renowned Oakville region, surrounded by a 42-acre estate vineyard highly regarded for the quality of its Cabernet Sauvignon.<br /><br /> ###</p>\n<p>PRESS CONTACTS:<br />Kim Koury/ Rosalind Napoli<br />Spin Public Relations<br />323-330-9559<br />kim@spinprgroup.com <br />rosalind@spinprgroup.com&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','local','2014-03-04','published'),
	(12,3,NULL,'Del Frisco?s Grilles in Houston and Fort Worth  Named to OpenTable?s List of the 100 Hottest Restaurants in the Country','Glodow Nead ','<p><strong>Top 100 restaurants were distinguished by OpenTable, which analyzed 5 million reviews of 19,000 restaurants</strong></p>\n<p>SOUTHLAKE, Texas (March 20, 2014) &mdash;Del Frisco&rsquo;s Restaurant Group is pleased to announce that two restaurants in its portfolio have been named to OpenTable&rsquo;s Top 100 Hot Spot Restaurant list for 2014 in the United States. &nbsp;Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grilles in Houston and Fort Worth were honored as part of the prestigious user-generated ranking. &nbsp;Based in Southlake, Texas, just outside Dallas, Del Frisco\'s Restaurant Group is a collection of 40 restaurants located across the country, including Del Frisco\'s Grille, Del Frisco\'s Double Eagle Steak House, and Sullivan\'s Steakhouse.</p>\n<p>The OpenTable Top 100 Hot Spot Restaurant list is a result of the collective opinions of more than five million reviews submitted by verified OpenTable guests for more than 19,000 restaurants in all 50 states and the District of Columbia. &nbsp;The list is part of OpenTable&rsquo;s Diners&rsquo; Choice ratings, which are compilations of member reviews organized into &ldquo;Best Of&rdquo; lists. &nbsp;Diners&rsquo; Choice ratings only use feedback from guests who were &ldquo;seated&rdquo; for their reservation (as opposed to those who didn&rsquo;t show), and the data is continuously refreshed for unbiased feedback.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille is an exciting eatery dishing up creative twists on American comfort classics. &nbsp;In 2012, Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille was honored by Nation&rsquo;s Restaurant News as the winner of the 18th annual Hot Concepts Award. &nbsp;Fans of Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille flock to the restaurant for favorites like Ahi Tuna Tacos, Cheesesteak Eggrolls, hand-crafted flatbreads, hearty salads, formidable sandwiches and prime steaks. &nbsp;Even late-night revelers get up early for a decadent weekend brunch at the Grille that includes an out-of-this-world Red Velvet Belgian Waffle and Chicken Fried Steak &amp; Eggs with Chorizo Gravy.</p>\n<p>With 300 selections from the Grille&rsquo;s sleek &ldquo;wine wall,&rdquo; Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille offers a wide variety of choices that appeal to every palate from the adventurous to the traditional. &nbsp;Del Frisco&rsquo;s Wine Director, David O&rsquo;Day, has carefully selected wines from established and up-and-coming regions in the world, creating an unparalleled and adventurous wine list, surprisingly more extensive than those found in a traditional bar and grill.</p>\n<p>&ldquo;Having two restaurants earn a place on OpenTable&rsquo;s Top 100 Hot Spot list is an incredible honor for the entire Del Frisco&rsquo;s Restaurant Group family,&rdquo; said Mark S. Mednansky, CEO of Del Frisco&rsquo;s Restaurant Group. &nbsp;&ldquo;We pride ourselves on not being a &lsquo;cookie cutter&rsquo; restaurant group, so Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grilles in Houston and Fort Worth have diverse menus that reflect the local taste of each city. &nbsp;We are grateful to our guests who use OpenTable for propelling us into the Top 100 list.&rdquo;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille in Houston is ideally located in the West Avenue retail center in the heart of the city&rsquo;s River Oaks district. &nbsp;Executive Chef Jeff Taylor has added market fresh, regional dishes to his menu, including Blackened Texas Gulf Redfish, Buffalo Style Grit Cakes and Cast Iron Pork &amp; Beans. &nbsp;Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille is located at 2800 Kirby Drive at Westheimer Road in Houston and the phone number is 832-623-6168.</p>\n<p>Just up the road in Fort Worth, the locals keep lining up for regional dishes like Stone Ground Grits with Cajun Lobster Sauce and Pepper Jack Tamales. &nbsp;Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille in Fort Worth is adjacent to the popular Sundance Square Plaza, a 35-block retail and entertainment district in the heart of the city. &nbsp;Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille is located at 154 E 3rd Street in Fort Worth and the phone number is 817-887-9900.</p>\n<p><strong>About Del Frisco\'s Restaurant Group</strong></p>\n<p>Del Frisco\'s Grille is owned by Del Frisco\'s Restaurant Group (NASDAQ: DFRG). &nbsp;Based in Southlake, Texas, near Dallas, Del Frisco\'s Restaurant Group is a collection of 40 restaurants located across the country, including Del Frisco\'s Grille, Del Frisco\'s Double Eagle Steak House, and Sullivan\'s Steakhouse. &nbsp;Del Frisco\'s Double Eagle Steak House serves up flawless cuisine that\'s bold and delicious, an extensive award-winning wine list and a level of service that reminds guests that they\'re the boss. &nbsp;Sullivan\'s Steakhouse is a great place to wine and dine any night of the week - with outstanding food, hand-shaken martinis, an award winning wine list, and live entertainment all under one roof. &nbsp;Del Frisco\'s Grille is modern, inviting, stylish and fun, taking the classic bar and grill to new heights, and drawing inspiration from bold flavors and market-fresh ingredients. &nbsp;All of the restaurants create a seamless dining experience for savvy business and leisure travelers who regularly dine or entertain away from home.</p>\n<p><strong>About OpenTable</strong></p>\n<p>OpenTable is a leading provider of free, real-time online restaurant reservations for diners and reservation and guest management solutions for restaurants. The OpenTable network delivers the convenience of online restaurant reservations to diners and the operational benefits of a computerized reservation book to restaurants. OpenTable has more than 27,000 restaurant customers, and, since its inception in 1998, has seated more than 400 million diners around the world. The company is headquartered in San Francisco, California, and the OpenTable service is available throughout the United States, as well as in Canada, Germany, Japan, Mexico, and the United Kingdom. OpenTable also owns and operates toptable.com, a leading restaurant reservation site in the United Kingdom.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>###</p>\n<p>Media Contact: Casey Shaughnessy at Glodow Nead Communications; 415-394-6500, ext. 212 or Casey@glodownead.com</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','national','2014-03-20','published'),
	(13,2,14,'RAISING THE ?STEAKS? SULLIVAN?S STEAKHOUSE UNVEILS A NEW CONTEMPORARY DESIGN ','Crown PR','<p><strong>Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse in Charlotte debuts a refreshed and youthful look after interior and exterior renovations</strong></p>\n<p>CHARLOTTE, N.C. (March 24, 2014) &ndash; Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse, a longtime Charlotte favorite known for its hand-cut steaks, fresh seafood and delectable side dishes, is debuting a significant facelift. Major renovations are complete on the bar and lounge, main dining area, private dining rooms, patio and more.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Sullivan&rsquo;s refreshed, contemporary design features a more vibrant color scheme. Design elements such as dramatic artwork and lighting bring a more energetic feel to the 9,045-square-foot restaurant. High-top stools surrounding a rustic communal dining table encourage mingling and conversation in the bar and lounge, which now seats 46 guests. &nbsp;And just in time for spring, Sullivan&rsquo;s expanded its al fresco dining with an enlarged patio and new outdoor seating. A sleek new awning creates a prominent outdoor presence in bustling South End.</p>\n<p>&ldquo;We are so excited to show off our new look to our loyal guests,&rdquo; said Rick Crowe, general manager of Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse. &ldquo;Sullivan&rsquo;s is a great place to wine and dine any night of the week, and our fresh new look reflects the personality and energy of our savvy guests.&rdquo;</p>\n<p>Guests will immediately notice a difference when they enter the restaurant with its new, bright foyer. &nbsp;Hand-crafted artwork includes pops of deep red and gold around the bar. Handsome dark woods and residential-inspired detailing juxtaposed with champagne accents and contemporary, clean lines create a visually lavish ambiance in the lounge. &nbsp;</p>\n<p>Along with its vibrant new look, Sullivan&rsquo;s refreshed its menu. Highlighted by Sullivan&rsquo;s favorites and seasonal picks, lunch entrees start at $14, entr&eacute;e salads begin at $12.50 and sandwiches begin at $10. For dinner, Sullivan&rsquo;s offers an a la carte selection of savory starters, fresh soups and greens, and delicious entrees for dinner, as well as the new Sure Thing, a $39 three-course prix fixe menu. &nbsp;Featured items include: Cheesesteak Eggrolls; the sweet, spicy and unforgettable Crispy Shanghai Calamari; Jumbo Shrimp Cocktail; and the new Braised Beef Ravioli. &nbsp;</p>\n<p>New seasonal picks source the freshest ingredients and presently includes an array of stone crab claws and a Kale salad. Sullivan&rsquo;s offers an impressive selection of wine, local craft beers on tap and a full bar. Its signature Knockout cocktail never fails to impress.</p>\n<p>Sullivan&rsquo;s is open for lunch from 11:30 a.m. &ndash; 2 p.m. Monday through Friday. Dinner is served from &nbsp;p.m. to &nbsp;11 p.m. Monday through Saturday and from 4:30 p.m. until 10 p.m. Sunday. &nbsp;The bar opens at 11:30 a.m. weekdays and 4:30 p.m. Saturday and Sunday and is open until late into the evening nightly.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse is at 1928 South Blvd, Charlotte, N.C. 28203. To learn more, please visit www.sullivanssteakhouse.com or call (704) 335.8228 for reservations and additional information.</p>\n<p><strong>About Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse</strong></p>\n<p>Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse, founded in 1996, is a favorite neighborhood restaurant. Known for its hand-cut steaks, Sullivan&rsquo;s is equally well-known for its fresh seafood, delectable side dishes, mouthwatering desserts and award-winning wine list. Sullivan&rsquo;s is the perfect place to wine and dine any night of the week &ndash; with food, drinks and live entertainment under one roof. Each Sullivan&rsquo;s features live music in the bar area nightly, delicious artisan cocktails, and exceptional food and wine.</p>\n<p>Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse is the sister restaurant to the renowned Del Frisco&rsquo;s Double Eagle Steak House and Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille, all of which are owned by Del Frisco&rsquo;s Restaurant Group (NASDAQ: DFRG) of Southlake, Texas. There are 19 Sullivan&rsquo;s across the country, which creates a seamless dining experience for savvy business travelers. Sullivan&rsquo;s retains its Southern roots, offering true Southern hospitality at each and every location.</p>\n<p>###</p>\n<p>Media contact for Sullivan&rsquo;s Steakhouse: &nbsp;Kathryn Blanchard, 704.906.0063, kblanchard@crown-com.com</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','local','2014-03-24','published'),
	(14,3,43,'DEL FRISCO?S GRILLE TO OPEN ITS FIRST OC LOCATION  NEXT MONTH AT IRVINE SPECTRUM','Elizabeth Borsting PR','<p><strong><em>Award-winning Restaurant Invites Guests to Meat Up, Drink Up with its Contemporary Menu of American Classics and List of Playful Libations</em></strong></p>\n<p>Irvine, Calif.&mdash;(July 10, 2014)&mdash; Texas-based Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille is bringing its award-winning concept to Orange County this summer and will make its debut at Irvine Spectrum Center on August 9. &nbsp; Taking the classic bar and grill to new heights, Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille is known for its bold flavors and market fresh ingredients evidenced in its menu of updated American classics for lunch, dinner and Sunday brunch.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&ldquo;We&rsquo;re very excited to introduce our concept to Orange County,&rdquo; said Mark S. Mednansky, CEO of Del Frisco&rsquo;s Restaurant Group. &nbsp;&ldquo;Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille is a dress up or dress down kind of place where you&rsquo;re welcome to come as you are for a casual meal or a prime steak dinner. &nbsp;We want our guests to have a fun and memorable dining experience.&rdquo; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The restaurant, built from the ground up and located adjacent to Nordstrom, boasts warm wood accents, acoustic panels embellished with brass beads, and clusters of glass bulbs that illuminate muted brass fixtures. &nbsp;Beyond the threshold is a striking &ldquo;glass box&rdquo; entryway that dramatically showcases the superb collection of wine. &nbsp;Spanning 8,000 square feet with a guest capacity of 290 for both indoor and outdoor seating, Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille also includes a collection of ample-size booths, tables and communal seating set in an open and lofty space. &nbsp;An industrial curtain of steel mesh divides the island bar from the main dining room. &nbsp;With plenty of seating at the island bar, guests can belly up for a complete meal and signature cocktail or opt for a table on the spacious open-air patio warmed by a striking outdoor fireplace. &nbsp;The Sun Room, an alcove located just off the main dining room, is bathed in natural sunlight by day with ambient lighting illuminating the space in the evening, and provides an exceptional backdrop for lunch, dinner or brunch. &nbsp;A more intimate dining nook, inspired by the popular chef&rsquo;s table concept, is located directly off the kitchen and offers an intimate space for special occasions. &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Behind the kitchen door is Juan Carlos Murillo, a veteran Orange County chef, who began his restaurant career in 1997 just a few miles away. &nbsp;Chef Murillo and his staff will present a menu of appetizers and shareable plates including Cheesesteak Eggrolls, Ahi Tacos and Fire Roasted Artichoke with Meyer Lemon vinaigrette, parmesan and black pepper aioli. &nbsp;The Jumbo Lump Crabcake is mostly all crab and very little cake served with a Cajun lobster sauce. &nbsp;A selection of flatbreads include the Wild Mushroom with caramelized onions, Fontina cheese, and baby arugula; and Pepperoni and Sausage topped with mozzarella and fresh tomato then dusted with parmesan cheese. &nbsp;There&rsquo;s also a selection of entr&eacute;e-sized salads, a selection of modern comfort foods, including meatloaf made from veal with hand-mashed potatoes and wild mushrooms topped with a bordelaise sauce as well as the popular Steamed Brown Bag Fish served with local vegetables. &nbsp;Two-fisted sandwiches include the Cali Chicken Sandwich served on challah bread and topped with crushed avocado, lettuce, tomato and lemon-tarragon mayonnaise. &nbsp; A selection of burgers, fresh seafood and signature steaks wet aged for 28 days round out the menu along with a series of side dishes that includes a decadent Truffle Mac and Cheese.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&ldquo;Guests are welcome to come in for a full meal or nothing more than dessert,&rdquo; said General Manager Katie Pavkov, an Orange County native and alumna of Chapman University who recently returned to the region after spending 12 years managing restaurants in south Florida. &nbsp;&ldquo;And our desserts are rather amazing, too, from our Coconut Cream Pie and six-layer Lemon Doberge Cake to Nutella Bread Pudding with caramel sauce and Warm Chocolate Cake served with vanilla bean ice cream and raspberry sauce. &nbsp;They&rsquo;re exceptionally decadent, which is how dessert should be.&rdquo; &nbsp;</p>\n<p>Sunday brunch, served until 3pm, features some morning favorites, including Red Velvet Belgian Waffle with whipped vanilla bean-spiked cream cheese and thick-cut hickory smoked bacon and The Grille Benedict with poached eggs, thinly-sliced French ham, and scallion and white cheddar biscuits topped with chipotle hollandaise sauce. &nbsp;Build-Your-Own Bloody Mary lets guests assume the role of cocktail impresario with an assembly of ingredients that includes house-made Bloody Mary mix presented in a glass milk jug along with Tito&rsquo;s Vodka and a plate of garnishes for taste and presentation.</p>\n<p>The Grille&rsquo;s calling card is its toast-worthy wine, which includes some 300 regional and global vintages along with two taps at the bar, which will pour a white wine and a refreshing house-made sangria. &nbsp;Wine on tap is becoming increasingly more popular because it restricts oxygen from coming in contact with the wine, which keeps the notes more pure and crisp. &nbsp;Signature cocktails, with eyebrow-raising names, such as Apt 5D, Kilt Lifter and The Morning After, are handmade and muddled using fresh ingredients and creative pairings. &nbsp;The VIP is a Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille original made with sweet Hawaiian pineapple-infused Svedka Clementine Vodka. &nbsp;Those watching their waistlines can enjoy a Skinny Cosmo weighing in at a little more than 200 calories. &nbsp;The Adult Milkshake, a grown-ups only indulgence, is equal parts dessert and cocktail with Nocello Walnut Liqueur, Cr&egrave;me de Cacao Chocolate Liqueur, and vanilla ice cream.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>This will be the second Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille to open in California and the first to debut in Orange County. &nbsp; The winner of Nation&rsquo;s Restaurant News 2012 Hot Concept Award, Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille at Irvine Spectrum will open its doors to the public on Saturday, August 9 at 4pm. &nbsp; Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grille at Irvine Spectrum Center, located adjacent to Nordstrom, is open for lunch Monday-Friday from 11am-4pm and until 3pm on Saturday with dinner served Monday-Friday 4-11pm, 3-11pm on Saturday, and 3-10pm on Sunday. &nbsp;Sunday brunch is served from 11am-3pm. &nbsp;For more information, visit www.delfriscosgrille.com.</p>\n<p>###</p>\n<p><strong>About Del Frisco\'s Grille</strong></p>\n<p>Del Frisco\'s Grille is modern, inviting, stylish and fun. Taking the classic bar and grill to new heights, Del Frisco\'s Grille draws inspiration from bold flavors and market-fresh ingredients. The energetic bar, a destination in itself, creates a buzz throughout the restaurant and sets the stage for an amazing night out. &nbsp;There are 12 Del Frisco&rsquo;s Grilles located across the country. It is the proud winner of the 2012 Hot Concepts Award presented annually by Nation&rsquo;s Restaurant News. For more information, visit http://delfriscosgrille.com.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>About Del Frisco\'s Restaurant Group</p>\n<p>Del Frisco\'s Grille is owned by Del Frisco\'s Restaurant Group (NASDAQ: DFRG). &nbsp;Based in Southlake, Texas, near Dallas, Del Frisco\'s Restaurant Group is a collection of more than 40 restaurants located across the country, including Del Frisco\'s Grille, Del Frisco\'s Double Eagle Steak House, and Sullivan\'s Steakhouse. &nbsp;Del Frisco\'s Double Eagle Steak House serves up flawless cuisine that\'s bold and delicious, an extensive award-winning wine list and a level of service that reminds guests that they\'re the boss. &nbsp;Sullivan\'s Steakhouse is a great place for a big night out on the town - with outstanding food, hand-shaken martinis, an award winning wine list, and live entertainment all under one roof. &nbsp;All of the restaurants create a seamless dining experience for savvy business and leisure travelers who regularly dine or entertain away from home. For more information, visit http://dfrg.com.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','local','2014-07-10','published'),
	(15,1,5,'Del Frisco?s Double Eagle Steak House Fort Worth  General Manager Greg Kalina Promoted to Regional Manager','Del Frisco\'s Restaurant Group ','<p><em>Fort Worth, TX (August 4, 2014)</em>&mdash; Del Frisco&rsquo;s Restaurant Group, Inc. (NASDAQ: DFRG), based in Southlake, Texas, announced today it has promoted Greg Kalina to Regional Manager for Del Frisco&rsquo;s Double Eagle Steak House.</p>\n<p>Kalina will oversee operations for two iconic Del Frisco&rsquo;s Double Eagle Steak Houses in Dallas and Fort Worth and report to Del Frisco&rsquo;s Restaurant Group COO Jeff Carcara.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&ldquo;Greg&rsquo;s contributions have been invaluable and he embodies so many of the wonderful traits of our company. His warm hospitality, team leadership and community involvement will continue to enhance the strategic direction and growth of the Del Frisco&rsquo;s brand,&rdquo; said Del Frisco&rsquo;s Restaurant Group CEO Mark S. Mednansky.</p>\n<p>Mr. Kalina joined Del Frisco&rsquo;s Restaurant Group in August 2006 after a 7-year stint as director of operations for a boutique restaurant group. &nbsp; His focus at the historical Fort Worth location downtown has been commitment to quality which has been well received from their clientele as well as from his team members. &nbsp;Kalina understands that nurturing individual employees ultimately benefits the entire company. &nbsp; &ldquo;We know that today&rsquo;s team members are tomorrow&rsquo;s leaders, so we do all that we can to support and encourage their personal growth so they can develop a strong sense of personal pride and accomplishment to support our company&rsquo;s growth,&rdquo; said Kalina.</p>\n<p>Del Frisco&rsquo;s Restaurant Group encourages all employees to stay active in the community and Kalina is passionately engaged. &nbsp; He sits on the boards of A Wish with Wings, Bobby Bragan Youth Foundation, and the Fort Worth Stock Show Syndicate. Kalina has chaired the Big Taste of Fort Worth, benefiting Big Brothers/Big Sisters, for five years and is a director on the board governing the Fort Worth Convention and Visitor&rsquo;s Bureau.</p>\n<p>This hometown hero also chairs the Fort Worth ISD Teaching Chairs of Excellence, which honors standout educators in the school district. &nbsp; Each fall, Del Frisco&rsquo;s Double Eagle Steak House holds its own Del Frisco&rsquo;s Invitational at Mira Vista Country Club benefiting One Safe Place, the Safe City Commission&rsquo;s new family justice project and hosts A Wish with Wings Annual Holiday Luncheon at the Steak House. &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Del Frisco&rsquo;s Double Eagle Steak House is located in downtown Fort Worth at 812 Main St., Fort Worth, Texas, 76102. The restaurant serves Dinner Mon-Thurs 5:00 pm - 10 pm; Fri 5:00 pm - 11 pm; and Sun 5:00 pm - 9:00 pm.</p>\n<p>For more information, please visit Del Frisco&rsquo;s Steak House online at www.delfriscos.com, call (817) 877-3999 or like us on Facebook at www.facebook.com/delsftworth</p>\n<p><strong>About Del Frisco&rsquo;s Double Eagle Steak House</strong>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>No one does steak like Del Frisco&rsquo;s Double Eagle Steak House. &nbsp;An American culinary institution, Del Frisco&rsquo;s serves up flawless cuisine that&rsquo;s bold and delicious, an extensive award-winning wine list and a level of service that reminds guests that they&rsquo;re the boss. &nbsp;Offering prime steak, fresh-off-the-boat seafood and genuine hospitality, Del Frisco&rsquo;s is an exceptional steak house, unparalleled in any city.</p>\n<p>Del Frisco\'s Double Eagle Steak House has been recognized nationally and has received the DiRoNA &nbsp; Award for Distinguished Restaurants of North America; Nation&rsquo;s Restaurant News Fine Dining Hall of Fame; Restaurants and Institutions&rsquo; Ivy Award; and the Wine Spectator Best of Award of Excellence for its extensive wine list.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>About Del Frisco\'s Restaurant Group</strong>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Del Frisco\'s Restaurant Group (NASDAQ: DFRG). Based in Southlake, Texas, near Dallas, Del Frisco\'s Restaurant Group is a collection of more than 40 restaurants located across the country, including Del Frisco\'s Grille, Del Frisco\'s Double Eagle Steak House, and Sullivan\'s Steakhouse. Del Frisco\'s Double Eagle Steak House serves up flawless cuisine that\'s bold and delicious, an extensive award-winning wine list and a level of service that reminds guests that they\'re the boss. Sullivan\'s Steakhouse is a great place for a big night out on the town - with outstanding food, hand-shaken martinis, an award winning wine list, and live entertainment all under one roof. All of the restaurants create a seamless dining experience for savvy business and leisure travelers who regularly dine or entertain away from home.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','local','2014-08-04','published');
